netappModuleId.name: netappModuleId
netappModuleId.description: The mib module for NetApp SNMPv2 entities

TimeTicks64.name: TimeTicks64
TimeTicks64.description: Represents time in hundredths (1/100) of a second since an epoch.

clusterIdentityName.name: clusterIdentityName
clusterIdentityName.description: Name of the cluster of which this node is a member.

nodeTable.name: nodeTable
nodeTable.description: Table of all nodes in the cluster.

nodeEntry.name: nodeEntry
nodeEntry.description: Entry for a node in the cluster.

nodeName.name: nodeName
nodeName.description: Node Name. Same as sysName for a specific node.

nodeOwner.name: nodeOwner
nodeOwner.description: Node Owner. Same as sysContact for a specific node.

nodeLocation.name: nodeLocation
nodeLocation.description: Node Location. Same as sysLocation for a specific node.

nodeModel.name: nodeModel
nodeModel.description: Node Model. Same as productModel for a specific node.

nodeSerialNumber.name: nodeSerialNumber
nodeSerialNumber.description: Node Serial Number. Same as productSerialNum for a specific node.

nodeAssetTag.name: nodeAssetTag
nodeAssetTag.description: Value of customer-assigned asset tag for this node.

nodeUptime.name: nodeUptime
nodeUptime.description: Node Uptime. Same as sysUpTime for a specific node.

nodeSystemId.name: nodeSystemId
nodeSystemId.description: Node System ID. Same as productId for a specific node.

nodeVendor.name: nodeVendor
nodeVendor.description: Node Vendor. Similar to productVendor for a specific node.

nodeHealth.name: nodeHealth
nodeHealth.description: Whether or not the node can communicate with the cluster.

nodeEligibility.name: nodeEligibility
nodeEligibility.description: An eligible node is one that has been designated by the administrator as an active participant in the cluster.

nodeEpsilon.name: nodeEpsilon
nodeEpsilon.description: Whether or not this node has epsilon to keep the quorum up if only half of the nodes can communicate.

nodeUuid.name: nodeUuid
nodeUuid.description: Universally unique identifier (UUID) of the node.

nodeCpuUptime.name: nodeCpuUptime
nodeCpuUptime.description: The time (in hundredths of a second) that the CPU has been up since the last boot.

nodeCpuBusyTime.name: nodeCpuBusyTime
nodeCpuBusyTime.description: The time (in hundredths of a second) that the CPU has been doing useful work since the last boot.

nodeNvramBatteryStatus.name: nodeNvramBatteryStatus
nodeNvramBatteryStatus.description: An indication of the current status of the NVRAM battery or batteries. Batteries which are fully or partially discharged may not fully protect the system during a crash. The end-of-life status values are based on the manufacturer's recommended life for the batteries.

nodeEnvOverTemperature.name: nodeEnvOverTemperature
nodeEnvOverTemperature.description: An indication of whether the hardware is currently operating outside of its recommended temperature range. The hardware will shutdown if the temperature exceeds critical thresholds.

nodeEnvFailedFanCount.name: nodeEnvFailedFanCount
nodeEnvFailedFanCount.description: Count of the number of chassis fans which are not operating within the recommended RPM range.

nodeEnvFailedFanMessage.name: nodeEnvFailedFanMessage
nodeEnvFailedFanMessage.description: Text message describing the current condition of chassis fans. This is useful only if envFailedFanCount is not zero.

nodeEnvFailedPowerSupplyCount.name: nodeEnvFailedPowerSupplyCount
nodeEnvFailedPowerSupplyCount.description: Count of the number of power supplies which are in degraded mode.

nodeEnvFailedPowerSupplyMessage.name: nodeEnvFailedPowerSupplyMessage
nodeEnvFailedPowerSupplyMessage.description: Text message describing the state of any power supplies which are currently degraded. This is useful only if envFailedPowerSupplyCount is not zero.

nodeProductVersion.name: nodeProductVersion
nodeProductVersion.description: Node Product Version. Similar to productVersion for a specific node.

nodeFirmwareVersion.name: nodeFirmwareVersion
nodeFirmwareVersion.description: Node Firmware Version. Similar to productFirmwareVersion for a specific node.

clusterLicenseEntry.name: clusterLicenseEntry
clusterLicenseEntry.description: Details about each installed cluster license.

clusterLicenseFeature.name: clusterLicenseFeature
clusterLicenseFeature.description: Cluster license feature ID, see clusterLicenseDescription for the name/description of this feature

clusterLicenseLimit.name: clusterLicenseLimit
clusterLicenseLimit.description: Cluster feature limit value. The units of this value are feature specific, for example number of nodes, capacity in TB, number of streams, etc. Information about this limit will be in the clusterLicenseDescription.

clusterLicenseExpirationDate.name: clusterLicenseExpirationDate
clusterLicenseExpirationDate.description: Cluster License Expiration Date if it exists

licensePackage.name: licensePackage
licensePackage.description: License package ID, see licenseDescription for the name/description of this package

licenseOwner.name: licenseOwner
licenseOwner.description: Name of the Node or Cluster that the license belongs to

licenseExpiration.name: licenseExpiration
licenseExpiration.description: License Expiration Date if it exists

licenseLegacy.name: licenseLegacy
licenseLegacy.description: Indicates if the license is a Legacy License

vserverUuid.name: vserverUuid
vserverUuid.description: Universally unique identifier (UUID) of virtual server.

vserverAggregate.name: vserverAggregate
vserverAggregate.description: Name of aggregate the vserver's root volume is in.

vserverNsSwitch.name: vserverNsSwitch
vserverNsSwitch.description: Vserver Name Service Switch setting (eg: nis, ldap, file).

vserverLanguage.name: vserverLanguage
vserverLanguage.description: Language of this vserver's volumes. For example, 'English'

vserverComment.name: vserverComment
vserverComment.description: Customer assigned comment for this vserver

vserverQuotaPolicy.name: vserverQuotaPolicy
vserverQuotaPolicy.description: Quota Policy assigned for all volumes in this vserver

vserverType.name: vserverType
vserverType.description: Type of the vserver. There are four distinct supported types: data, admin, node and system. 'data' vservers are the default scale-out vservers. One 'admin' vserver exists per cluster and it provides universal administrative access to the cluster. One 'node' vserver exists per node in the cluster and identifies the physical controller. 'system' vserver is for cluster-scoped communications in an IPspace.

vserverAggrList.name: vserverAggrList
vserverAggrList.description: This is a comma-separated list of aggregates on which the Vserver can perform volume operations. The aggregates may be shared for use with other Vservers.

vserverAllowedProtocolList.name: vserverAllowedProtocolList
vserverAllowedProtocolList.description: This is a comma-separated list of protocols/services allowed to run on the Vserver. Eg: NFS,CIFS,iSCSI,FCP.

vserverNumVolumes.name: vserverNumVolumes
vserverNumVolumes.description: Number of volumes that are contained in the Vserver.

vserverMaxVolumes.name: vserverMaxVolumes
vserverMaxVolumes.description: Maximum number of volumes that can be created on the Vserver.

vserverDisallowedProtocolList.name: vserverDisallowedProtocolList
vserverDisallowedProtocolList.description: This is a comma-separated list of protocols/services disallowed to run on the Vserver. Eg: NFS,CIFS,iSCSI,FCP.

vserverIPspace.name: vserverIPspace
vserverIPspace.description: IPspace where the Vserver is assigned.

vserverIsRepository.name: vserverIsRepository
vserverIsRepository.description: This Vserver is a Vserver with Infinite Volume. A Vserver with Infinite Volume contains a single Infinite Volume.

productType.name: productType
productType.description: The product type representing the target platform.

productVersion.name: productVersion
productVersion.description: Version String for the Software Running on this platform.

productId.name: productId
productId.description: The System ID of this system.

productVendor.name: productVendor
productVendor.description: The vendor id of this system, indicating the company that has supplied the product.

productModel.name: productModel
productModel.description: The model name of the system. Examples are FAS980 and FAS3050.

productFirmwareVersion.name: productFirmwareVersion
productFirmwareVersion.description: Version string for the Firmware running on this platform.

productGuiUrl.name: productGuiUrl
productGuiUrl.description: The complete URL used to access the administrative GUI for a browser-based interface.

productApiUrl.name: productApiUrl
productApiUrl.description: The complete URL used to access the administrative API for a programmatic interface.

productSerialNum.name: productSerialNum
productSerialNum.description: The product serial number. Returns unknown if it cannot be determined.

productPartnerSerialNum.name: productPartnerSerialNum
productPartnerSerialNum.description: The partner's serial number, not applicable if there is no partner, and unknown if it cannot be determined.

productCPUArch.name: productCPUArch
productCPUArch.description: The CPU architecture type of this appliance

productTrapData.name: productTrapData
productTrapData.description: This returns a static string. This object is used as a placeholder for enterprise traps.

productMachineType.name: productMachineType
productMachineType.description: The machine type of the system. Examples are FAS980 and FAS3050.

productLicenseTable.name: productLicenseTable
productLicenseTable.description: Returns information about the current list of licensed services, the type of license, and, if it is a time limited license, the expiration date. It also tells the services that are not licensed for the appliance, or if a time limited licensed service has expired. It will also return whether or not the the service was automatically enabled due to business packaging policies based on platform type.

productLicenseIndex.name: productLicenseIndex
productLicenseIndex.description: Index into the product license table.

licenseIsLicensed.name: licenseIsLicensed
licenseIsLicensed.description: True if the service is licensed and has not expired, false otherwise.

licenseIsExpired.name: licenseIsExpired
licenseIsExpired.description: True if the promotional/time-expiring/demo license has expired, false otherwise.

licenseIsSite.name: licenseIsSite
licenseIsSite.description: True if the service is a site license, false otherwise.

licenseExpirationTimeStamp.name: licenseExpirationTimeStamp
licenseExpirationTimeStamp.description: Expected expiration timestamp in seconds since January 1, 1970, if it's a promotional/time-expiring license. 0 for all other licenses.

licenseIsAutoEnabled.name: licenseIsAutoEnabled
licenseIsAutoEnabled.description: True if the service is automatically licensed (licenseIsLicensed will also be True) false otherwise.

nodeStatTable.name: nodeStatTable
nodeStatTable.description: Table containing all counters in the cluster, organized on a per-node, per-category, per-object basis.

nodeStatEntry.name: nodeStatEntry
nodeStatEntry.description: Entry for a single counter in the cluster, on a per-node, per-category, per-object basis.

nodeStatNode.name: nodeStatNode
nodeStatNode.description: Node from which the counter is collected.

nodeStatInstanceIndex.name: nodeStatInstanceIndex
nodeStatInstanceIndex.description: Index of instance on which the counter exists.

nodeStatCounterIndex.name: nodeStatCounterIndex
nodeStatCounterIndex.description: Index of counter within this category.

nodeStatUnits.name: nodeStatUnits
nodeStatUnits.description: Units for this counter. Possible values include: 'B' (bytes), 's' (seconds), 'ms' (milliseconds), 'us' (microseconds), '%' (percent), or '' (none).

nodeStatCounterName.name: nodeStatCounterName
nodeStatCounterName.description: Name of counter within this category.

nodeStatLabels.name: nodeStatLabels
nodeStatLabels.description: List of counter labels. Used for counter arrays of if 'counter' value is not an integer.

nodeStatValues.name: nodeStatValues
nodeStatValues.description: List of values. Only used to for counter arrays.

cpuUpTime.name: cpuUpTime
cpuUpTime.description: The time (in hundredths of a second) that the CPU has been up since the last boot.

cpuBusyTime.name: cpuBusyTime
cpuBusyTime.description: The time (in hundredths of a second) that the CPU has been doing useful work since the last boot.

cpuBusyTimePerCent.name: cpuBusyTimePerCent
cpuBusyTimePerCent.description: The percent of time that the CPU has been doing useful work since the last time a client requested the cpuBusyTimePerCent.

cpuIdleTime.name: cpuIdleTime
cpuIdleTime.description: The time (in hundredths of a second) that the CPU has been idle since the last boot.

cpuIdleTimePerCent.name: cpuIdleTimePerCent
cpuIdleTimePerCent.description: The percent of time that the CPU has been idle since the last time a client requested the cpuBusyTimePerCent.

cpuCount.name: cpuCount
cpuCount.description: The number of CPUs in the system.

cpuContextSwitches.name: cpuContextSwitches
cpuContextSwitches.description: The number of hardware context switches.

cpuInterrupts.name: cpuInterrupts
cpuInterrupts.description: The number of interrupts during a CP.

cpuNonCPInterrupts.name: cpuNonCPInterrupts
cpuNonCPInterrupts.description: The number of interrupts not during a CP.

cpuCPInterruptPercent.name: cpuCPInterruptPercent
cpuCPInterruptPercent.description: The percentage of time handling CP interrupts.

cpuNonCPInterruptPercent.name: cpuNonCPInterruptPercent
cpuNonCPInterruptPercent.description: The percentage of time handling non-cp interrupts.

cpuTotalDomainSwitches.name: cpuTotalDomainSwitches
cpuTotalDomainSwitches.description: The total number of Domain Switches.

cDOTCpuTable.name: cDOTCpuTable
cDOTCpuTable.description: Provide a report of the current CPU statistics on per node basis

cDOTCpuEntry.name: cDOTCpuEntry
cDOTCpuEntry.description: Provide a report of the node's CPU statistics

cDOTCpuNodeName.name: cDOTCpuNodeName
cDOTCpuNodeName.description: Node Name. Same as nodeName for a specific node.

cDOTCpuUpTime.name: cDOTCpuUpTime
cDOTCpuUpTime.description: The time (in hundredths of a second) that the CPU has been up since the last boot.

cDOTCpuBusyTime.name: cDOTCpuBusyTime
cDOTCpuBusyTime.description: The time (in hundredths of a second) that the CPU has been doing useful work since the last boot.

cDOTCpuBusyTimePerCent.name: cDOTCpuBusyTimePerCent
cDOTCpuBusyTimePerCent.description: The percent of time that the CPU has been doing useful work since the last time a client requested the cDOTCpuBusyTimePerCent.

cDOTCpuIdleTime.name: cDOTCpuIdleTime
cDOTCpuIdleTime.description: The time (in hundredths of a second) that the CPU has been idle since the last boot.

cDOTCpuIdleTimePerCent.name: cDOTCpuIdleTimePerCent
cDOTCpuIdleTimePerCent.description: The percent of time that the CPU has been idle since the last time a client requested the cDOTCpuBusyTimePerCent.

cDOTCpuCount.name: cDOTCpuCount
cDOTCpuCount.description: The number of CPUs in the system.

cDOTCpuContextSwitches.name: cDOTCpuContextSwitches
cDOTCpuContextSwitches.description: The number of hardware context switches.

cDOTCpuInterrupts.name: cDOTCpuInterrupts
cDOTCpuInterrupts.description: The number of interrupts during a CP.

cDOTCpuNonCPInterrupts.name: cDOTCpuNonCPInterrupts
cDOTCpuNonCPInterrupts.description: The number of interrupts not during a CP.

cDOTCpuCPInterruptPercent.name: cDOTCpuCPInterruptPercent
cDOTCpuCPInterruptPercent.description: The percentage of time handling CP interrupts.

cDOTCpuNonCPInterruptPercent.name: cDOTCpuNonCPInterruptPercent
cDOTCpuNonCPInterruptPercent.description: The percentage of time handling non-cp interrupts.

cDOTCpuTotalDomainSwitches.name: cDOTCpuTotalDomainSwitches
cDOTCpuTotalDomainSwitches.description: The total number of Domain Switches.

miscNfsOps.name: miscNfsOps
miscNfsOps.description: The total number of Server side NFS calls since the last boot

miscNetRcvdKB.name: miscNetRcvdKB
miscNetRcvdKB.description: The total number of KBytes received on all the network interfaces, since the last boot.

miscNetSentKB.name: miscNetSentKB
miscNetSentKB.description: The total number of KBytes transmitted on all the network interfaces, since the last boot.

miscGlobalStatus.name: miscGlobalStatus
miscGlobalStatus.description: This indicates the overall status of the appliance. The algorithm to determine the value uses both hardware status (e.g. the number of failed fans) and volume status (e.g. number of volumes that are full). The algorithm is subject to change in future releases, but the range of values will not change.

miscHighNfsOps.name: miscHighNfsOps
miscHighNfsOps.description: The total number of Server side NFS calls since the last boot. This object returns the most significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use misc64NfsOps instead.

miscLowNfsOps.name: miscLowNfsOps
miscLowNfsOps.description: The total number of Server side NFS calls since the last boot. This object returns the least significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use misc64NfsOps instead.

miscHighCifsOps.name: miscHighCifsOps
miscHighCifsOps.description: The total number of Server side CIFS calls since the last boot. This object returns the most significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use misc64CifsOps instead.

miscLowCifsOps.name: miscLowCifsOps
miscLowCifsOps.description: The total number of Server side CIFS calls since the last boot. This object returns the least significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use misc64CifsOps instead.

miscHighHttpOps.name: miscHighHttpOps
miscHighHttpOps.description: The total number of HTTP operations received since the last boot. This object returns the most significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use misc64HttpOps instead.

miscLowHttpOps.name: miscLowHttpOps
miscLowHttpOps.description: The total number of HTTP operations received since the last boot. This object returns the least significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use misc64HttpOps instead.

miscHighNetRcvdBytes.name: miscHighNetRcvdBytes
miscHighNetRcvdBytes.description: The total number of bytes received on all the network interfaces, since the last boot. This object returns the most significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use misc64NetRcvdBytes instead.

miscLowNetRcvdBytes.name: miscLowNetRcvdBytes
miscLowNetRcvdBytes.description: The total number of bytes received on all the network interfaces, since the last boot. This object returns the least significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use misc64NetRcvdBytes instead.

miscHighNetSentBytes.name: miscHighNetSentBytes
miscHighNetSentBytes.description: The total number of bytes transmitted on all the network interfaces, since the last boot. This object returns the most significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use misc64NetSentBytes instead.

miscLowNetSentBytes.name: miscLowNetSentBytes
miscLowNetSentBytes.description: The total number of bytes transmitted on all the network interfaces, since the last boot. This object returns the least significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use misc64NetSentBytes instead.

miscHighDiskReadBytes.name: miscHighDiskReadBytes
miscHighDiskReadBytes.description: The total number of bytes read from disk since the last boot. This object returns the most significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use misc64DiskReadBytes instead.

miscLowDiskReadBytes.name: miscLowDiskReadBytes
miscLowDiskReadBytes.description: The total number of bytes read from disk since the last boot. This object returns the least significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use misc64DiskReadBytes instead.

miscHighDiskWriteBytes.name: miscHighDiskWriteBytes
miscHighDiskWriteBytes.description: The total number of bytes written to disk since the last boot. This object returns the most significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use misc64DiskWriteBytes instead.

miscLowDiskWriteBytes.name: miscLowDiskWriteBytes
miscLowDiskWriteBytes.description: The total number of bytes written to disk since the last boot. This object returns the least significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use misc64DiskWriteBytes instead.

miscHighTapeReadBytes.name: miscHighTapeReadBytes
miscHighTapeReadBytes.description: The total number of bytes read from tape since the last boot. This object returns the most significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use misc64TapeReadBytes instead.

miscLowTapeReadBytes.name: miscLowTapeReadBytes
miscLowTapeReadBytes.description: The total number of bytes read from tape since the last boot. This object returns the least significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use misc64TapeReadBytes instead.

miscHighTapeWriteBytes.name: miscHighTapeWriteBytes
miscHighTapeWriteBytes.description: The total number of bytes written to tape since the last boot. This object returns the most significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use misc64TapeWriteBytes instead.

miscLowTapeWriteBytes.name: miscLowTapeWriteBytes
miscLowTapeWriteBytes.description: The total number of bytes written to tape since the last boot. This object returns the least significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use misc64TapeWriteBytes instead.

miscCacheAge.name: miscCacheAge
miscCacheAge.description: Age in minutes of the oldest read-only blocks in the buffer cache. This indicates how fast read operations are cycling through system memory; when the appliance is reading very large files (larger than the machine's memory size), buffer cache age will be very low.

miscCorrectedMachineChecks.name: miscCorrectedMachineChecks
miscCorrectedMachineChecks.description: Number of corrected machine checks since the last boot.

miscGlobalStatusMessage.name: miscGlobalStatusMessage
miscGlobalStatusMessage.description: A string describing the global status, including a description of the condition (if any) that caused the status to be anything other than ok(3).

miscWindowsSetupWizardVersion.name: miscWindowsSetupWizardVersion
miscWindowsSetupWizardVersion.description: The version number of Windows Setup Wizard required to configure the appliance. Windows Setup Wizard with a version number lower than this integer is not capable of configuring the appliance.

misc64NfsOps.name: misc64NfsOps
misc64NfsOps.description: The total number of Server side NFS calls since the last boot. This object returns all of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

misc64CifsOps.name: misc64CifsOps
misc64CifsOps.description: The total number of Server side CIFS calls since the last boot. This object returns all of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

misc64HttpOps.name: misc64HttpOps
misc64HttpOps.description: The total number of HTTP operations received since the last boot. This object returns all of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

misc64NetRcvdBytes.name: misc64NetRcvdBytes
misc64NetRcvdBytes.description: The total number of bytes received on all the network interfaces, since the last boot. This object returns all of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

misc64NetSentBytes.name: misc64NetSentBytes
misc64NetSentBytes.description: The total number of bytes transmitted on all the network interfaces, since the last boot. This object returns all of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

misc64DiskReadBytes.name: misc64DiskReadBytes
misc64DiskReadBytes.description: The total number of bytes read from disk since the last boot. This object returns all of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

misc64DiskWriteBytes.name: misc64DiskWriteBytes
misc64DiskWriteBytes.description: The total number of bytes written to disk since the last boot. This object returns all of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

misc64TapeReadBytes.name: misc64TapeReadBytes
misc64TapeReadBytes.description: The total number of bytes read from tape since the last boot. This object returns all of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

misc64TapeWriteBytes.name: misc64TapeWriteBytes
misc64TapeWriteBytes.description: The total number of bytes written to tape since the last boot. This object returns all of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

cfSettings.name: cfSettings
cfSettings.description: Clustered Failover configuration settings. The value notConfigured(1) indicates that the cluster is not licensed. The thisNodeDead(5) setting indicates that this node has been taken over.

cfCannotTakeoverCause.name: cfCannotTakeoverCause
cfCannotTakeoverCause.description: The reason this node cannot takeover its partner

cfPartnerStatus.name: cfPartnerStatus
cfPartnerStatus.description: This is the status last returned by the Clustered Failover partner.

cfPartnerLastStatusUpdate.name: cfPartnerLastStatusUpdate
cfPartnerLastStatusUpdate.description: If non-zero, the absolute time of the last update from the Clustered Failover partner.

cfPartnerSysid.name: cfPartnerSysid
cfPartnerSysid.description: System ID for Clustered Failover partner.

cfInterconnectStatus.name: cfInterconnectStatus
cfInterconnectStatus.description: The current status of the interconnect. The partialFailure(3) status indicates that one of the links in the interconnect hardware is down.

envOverTemperature.name: envOverTemperature
envOverTemperature.description: An indication of whether the hardware is currently operating outside of its recommended temperature range. The hardware will shutdown if the temperature exceeds critical thresholds.

envFailedFanCount.name: envFailedFanCount
envFailedFanCount.description: Count of the number of chassis fans which are not operating within the recommended RPM range.

envFailedFanMessage.name: envFailedFanMessage
envFailedFanMessage.description: Text message describing the current condition of chassis fans. This is useful only if envFailedFanCount is not zero.

envFailedPowerSupplyCount.name: envFailedPowerSupplyCount
envFailedPowerSupplyCount.description: Count of the number of power supplies which are in degraded mode.

envFailedPowerSupplyMessage.name: envFailedPowerSupplyMessage
envFailedPowerSupplyMessage.description: Text message describing the state of any power supplies which are currently degraded. This is useful only if envFailedPowerSupplyCount is not zero.

nvramBatteryStatus.name: nvramBatteryStatus
nvramBatteryStatus.description: An indication of the current status of the NVRAM battery or batteries. Batteries which are fully or partially discharged may not fully protect the system during a crash. The end-of-life status values are based on the manufacturer's recommended life for the batteries.

cpTime.name: cpTime
cpTime.description: The time (in hundredths of a second) since boot during which the system has had a consistency point (cp) operation in progress.

cpFromTimerOps.name: cpFromTimerOps
cpFromTimerOps.description: The number of consistency point operations since boot that were caused by timer.

cpFromSnapshotOps.name: cpFromSnapshotOps
cpFromSnapshotOps.description: The number of consistency point operations since boot that were caused by snapshot operation.

cpFromLowWaterOps.name: cpFromLowWaterOps
cpFromLowWaterOps.description: The number of consistency point operations since boot that were caused by low water mark.

cpFromHighWaterOps.name: cpFromHighWaterOps
cpFromHighWaterOps.description: The number of consistency point operations since boot that were caused by high water mark.

cpFromLogFullOps.name: cpFromLogFullOps
cpFromLogFullOps.description: The number of consistency point operations since boot that were caused by nv-log full.

cpFromCpOps.name: cpFromCpOps
cpFromCpOps.description: The number of back to back consistency point operations since boot.

cpTotalOps.name: cpTotalOps
cpTotalOps.description: The total number of consistency point operations since boot.

cpFromFlushOps.name: cpFromFlushOps
cpFromFlushOps.description: The number of consistency point operations since boot that were caused by flushing unlogged write data.

cpFromSyncOps.name: cpFromSyncOps
cpFromSyncOps.description: The number of consistency point operations since boot that were caused by file system sync requests.

cpFromLowVbufOps.name: cpFromLowVbufOps
cpFromLowVbufOps.description: The number of consistency point operations since boot that were caused by low virtual buffers.

cpFromCpDeferredOps.name: cpFromCpDeferredOps
cpFromCpDeferredOps.description: The number of back to back consistency point operations since boot that were deferred.

cpFromLowDatavecsOps.name: cpFromLowDatavecsOps
cpFromLowDatavecsOps.description: The number of consistency point operations since boot that were caused by low datavecs.

cpFromLowMbufOps.name: cpFromLowMbufOps
cpFromLowMbufOps.description: The number of consistency point operations since boot that were caused by low mbufs.

cpFromNvlogReplayTakeoverTime.name: cpFromNvlogReplayTakeoverTime
cpFromNvlogReplayTakeoverTime.description: The number of consistency point operations since boot that were caused by nvlog replay takeover time.

cDOTCpTable.description: Provide a report of the current CP statistics on per node basis

cDOTCpEntry.description: Provide a report of the node's CP statistics

cDOTCpTime.description: The time (in hundredths of a second) since boot during which the system has had a consistency point (cp) operation in progress.

cDOTCpFromTimerOps.name: cDOTCpFromTimerOps
cDOTCpFromTimerOps.description: The number of consistency point operations since boot that were caused by timer.

cDOTCpFromSnapshotOps.description: The number of consistency point operations since boot that were caused by snapshot operation.

cDOTCpFromLowWaterOps.description: The number of consistency point operations since boot that were caused by low water mark.

cDOTCpFromHighWaterOps.name: cDOTCpFromHighWaterOps
cDOTCpFromHighWaterOps.description: The number of consistency point operations since boot that were caused by high water mark.

cDOTCpFromLogFullOps.description: The number of consistency point operations since boot that were caused by nv-log full.

cDOTCpFromCpOps.name: cDOTCpFromCpOps
cDOTCpFromCpOps.description: The number of back to back consistency point operations since boot.
