nfsIsLicensed.name: nfsIsLicensed
nfsIsLicensed.description: Whether the nfs protocol is licensed on the filer.

quotaState.name: quotaState
quotaState.description: Indicates whether the root volume's quotas are ON, OFF or initializing. This object is deprecated - use qvStateTable.qvStateStat instead.

quotaInitPercent.name: quotaInitPercent
quotaInitPercent.description: Indicates percentage of root volume quota computation done while quotas are in initializing state. This object is deprecated - use qvStateTable.qvInitPercent instead.

qrTable.name: qrTable
qrTable.description: Provide a report of the current file and space consumption for each user or group with a quota in /etc/quotas. All quotas are displayed regardless of volume, and no volume information is given. This table is deprecated - use qrVTable instead.

qrEntry.name: qrEntry
qrEntry.description: Provide a report of the current file and space consumption for a referenced entry with a quota in the file /etc/quotas. All quotas are displayed regardless of volume, and no volume information is given. This object is deprecated - use qrVEntry instead.

qrIndex.name: qrIndex
qrIndex.description: A number that identifies this entry in the file /etc/quotas.

qrType.name: qrType
qrType.description: Identifies the kind of quota for this qrEntry.

qrId.name: qrId
qrId.description: The UID (user's numerical ID) or the GID (numerical ID of the group that a user belongs to), as applicable, associated with this qrEntry.

qrKBytesUsed.name: qrKBytesUsed
qrKBytesUsed.description: The current number of KBytes used for this qrEntry.

qrKBytesLimit.name: qrKBytesLimit
qrKBytesLimit.description: The limit of KBytes that can be used for this qrEntry.

qrFilesUsed.name: qrFilesUsed
qrFilesUsed.description: The current number of files used for this qrEntry.

qrFileLimit.name: qrFileLimit
qrFileLimit.description: The limit of files that can be used for this qrEntry.

qrPathName.name: qrPathName
qrPathName.description: A textual string that contains the path corresponding to this qrEntry.

qvStateTable.name: qvStateTable
qvStateTable.description: Provide a report of the current quota state of each volume in the system.

qvStateEntry.name: qvStateEntry
qvStateEntry.description: Provide a report of the current quota state of each volume in the system.

qvStateVolume.name: qvStateVolume
qvStateVolume.description: A number that identifies this volume. The mapping of this number to actual volumes may change if volumes are added or deleted. Use qvStateName to unambiguously identify a volume. The mapping established by this object is the same as the mapping of qrVVolume (below) to actual volumes. For instance, if a qvStateVolume value of '5' represents the volume 'vol2', a value of '5' in qrVVolume also represents the volume 'vol2'.

qvStateName.name: qvStateName
qvStateName.description: Indicates the name of this volume.

qvStateStat.name: qvStateStat
qvStateStat.description: Indicates whether quotas are ON, OFF, initializing or corrupted

qvStateInitPercent.name: qvStateInitPercent
qvStateInitPercent.description: Indicates percentage of quota computation done while quotas are in initializing state.

qvStateVserver.name: qvStateVserver
qvStateVserver.description: Indicates the vserver to which the volume belongs. Name from the cluster interfaces. Only applicable to cluster-mode volume.

qrVTable.name: qrVTable
qrVTable.description: Provide a report of the current file and space consumption for each user or group with a quota in /etc/quotas.

qrVEntry.name: qrVEntry
qrVEntry.description: Provide a report of the current file and space consumption for a referenced entry with a quota in the file /etc/quotas. Indices select the volume of the quota and the quota entry itself.

qrVIndex.name: qrVIndex
qrVIndex.description: A number that identifies this entry in the file /etc/quotas in the given volume.

qrVType.name: qrVType
qrVType.description: Identifies the kind of quota for this qrVEntry.

qrVId.name: qrVId
qrVId.description: The UID (user's numerical ID) or the GID (numerical ID of the group that a user belongs to), as applicable, associated with this qrVEntry. Check the qrVIdType field to see if this field is valid.

qrVKBytesUsed.name: qrVKBytesUsed
qrVKBytesUsed.description: The current number of KBytes used for this qrVEntry.

qrVKBytesLimit.name: qrVKBytesLimit
qrVKBytesLimit.description: The limit of KBytes that can be used for this qrVEntry.

qrVFilesUsed.name: qrVFilesUsed
qrVFilesUsed.description: The current number of files used for this qrVEntry.

qrVFileLimit.name: qrVFileLimit
qrVFileLimit.description: The limit of files that can be used for this qrVEntry.

qrVPathName.name: qrVPathName
qrVPathName.description: A textual string that contains the path corresponding to this qrVEntry.

qrVVolume.name: qrVVolume
qrVVolume.description: A number that identifies the volume for which this quota is in effect on. The volume that this value represents can be determined by checking the value of qvStateName (above) with qvStateVolume set to the value found here.

qrVTree.name: qrVTree
qrVTree.description: A string that indicates which qtree this quota belongs to.

qrVIdType.name: qrVIdType
qrVIdType.description: A value that indicates which ID field is valid.

qrVSid.name: qrVSid
qrVSid.description: The one or more IDs associated with this qrVEntry. If the qrVentry is associated with a Windows ID, the text form of the Windows ID (the SID) is here. If the qrVEntry is associated with more than one id, this contains a blank separated list of those IDs. Check the qrVIdType field to see if this field is valid.

qrVKBytesThreshold.name: qrVKBytesThreshold
qrVKBytesThreshold.description: A number of KBytes that when used by this entry produces a warning message.

qrVKBytesLimitSoft.name: qrVKBytesLimitSoft
qrVKBytesLimitSoft.description: The limit of KBytes that can be used for this qrVEntry before a warning message and SNMP trap is produced.

qrVFileLimitSoft.name: qrVFileLimitSoft
qrVFileLimitSoft.description: The limit of files that can be used for this qrVEntry before a warning message and SNMP trap is produced.

qrV2Table.name: qrV2Table
qrV2Table.description: Provide a report of the current file and space consumption for each user or group with a quota in /etc/quotas.

qrV2Entry.name: qrV2Entry
qrV2Entry.description: Provide a report of the current file and space consumption for a referenced entry with a quota in the file /etc/quotas. Indices select the volume of the quota and the quota entry itself.

qrV2Index.name: qrV2Index
qrV2Index.description: A number that identifies this entry in the file /etc/quotas in the given volume.

qrV2Type.name: qrV2Type
qrV2Type.description: Identifies the kind of quota for this qrV2Entry.

qrV2Id.name: qrV2Id
qrV2Id.description: The UID (user's numerical ID) or the GID (numerical ID of the group that a user belongs to), as applicable, associated with this qrV2Entry. Check the qrV2IdType field to see if this field is valid.

qrV2HighKBytesUsed.name: qrV2HighKBytesUsed
qrV2HighKBytesUsed.description: The current number of KBytes used for this qrV2Entry. This object returns the most significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use qrV264KBytesUsed instead.

qrV2LowKBytesUsed.name: qrV2LowKBytesUsed
qrV2LowKBytesUsed.description: The current number of KBytes used for this qrV2Entry. This object returns the least significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use qrV264KBytesUsed instead.

qrV2QuotaUnlimited.name: qrV2QuotaUnlimited
qrV2QuotaUnlimited.description: This flag designates whether or not the size based quota limit for this qrV2Entry is unlimited. If false(1) then qrV2*KBytesLimit OID's are valid, if true(2) then qrV2*KBytesLimit OID's are unused and will return 0.

qrV2HighKBytesLimit.name: qrV2HighKBytesLimit
qrV2HighKBytesLimit.description: The limit of KBytes that can be used for this qrV2Entry. This object returns the most significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This will return 0 if qrV2QuotaUnlimited is true. This object is deprecated - Use qrV264KBytesLimit instead.

qrV2LowKBytesLimit.name: qrV2LowKBytesLimit
qrV2LowKBytesLimit.description: The limit of KBytes that can be used for this qrV2Entry. This object returns the least significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This will return 0 if qrV2QuotaUnlimited is true. This object is deprecated - Use qrV264KBytesLimit instead.

qrV2FilesUsed.name: qrV2FilesUsed
qrV2FilesUsed.description: The current number of files used for this qrV2Entry.

qrV2FileQuotaUnlimited.name: qrV2FileQuotaUnlimited
qrV2FileQuotaUnlimited.description: This flag designates whether or not the file based quota limit for this qrV2Entry is unlimited. If false(1) then qrV2FileLimit is valid, if true(2) qrV2FileLimit will return 0.

qrV2FileLimit.name: qrV2FileLimit
qrV2FileLimit.description: The limit of files that can be used for this qrV2Entry.

qrV2PathName.name: qrV2PathName
qrV2PathName.description: A textual string that contains the path corresponding to this qrV2Entry.

qrV2Volume.name: qrV2Volume
qrV2Volume.description: A number that identifies the volume for which this quota is in effect on. The volume that this value represents can be determined by checking the value of qvStateName (above) with qvStateVolume set to the value found here.

qrV2Tree.name: qrV2Tree
qrV2Tree.description: A string that indicates which qtree this quota belongs to.

qrV2IdType.name: qrV2IdType
qrV2IdType.description: A value that indicates which ID field is valid.

qrV2Sid.name: qrV2Sid
qrV2Sid.description: The one or more IDs associated with this qrV2Entry. If the qrV2entry is associated with a Windows ID, the text form of the Windows ID (the SID) is here. If the qrV2Entry is associated with more than one id, this contains a blank separated list of those IDs. Check the qrV2IdType field to see if this field is valid.

qrV2ThresholdUnlimited.name: qrV2ThresholdUnlimited
qrV2ThresholdUnlimited.description: This flag designates whether or not the size based threshold limit for this qrV2Entry is unlimited. If false(1) then qrV2*KBytesThreshold OID's are valid, if true(2) then qrV2*KBytesThreshold OID's are unused and will return 0.

qrV2HighKBytesThreshold.name: qrV2HighKBytesThreshold
qrV2HighKBytesThreshold.description: A number of KBytes that when used by this entry produces a warning message. This object returns the most significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This will return 0 if qrV2ThresholdUnlimited is true. This object is deprecated - Use qrV264KBytesThreshold instead.

qrV2LowKBytesThreshold.name: qrV2LowKBytesThreshold
qrV2LowKBytesThreshold.description: A number of KBytes that when used by this entry produces a warning message. This object returns the least significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This will return 0 if qrV2ThresholdUnlimited is true. This object is deprecated - Use qrV264KBytesThreshold instead.

qrV2SoftQuotaUnlimited.name: qrV2SoftQuotaUnlimited
qrV2SoftQuotaUnlimited.description: This flag designates whether or not the size based soft quota limit for this qrV2Entry is unlimited. If false(1) then qrV2*KBytesSoftLimit OID's are valid, if true(2) the qrV2*KBytesSoftLimit OID's are unused and will return 0.

qrV2HighKBytesSoftLimit.name: qrV2HighKBytesSoftLimit
qrV2HighKBytesSoftLimit.description: The limit of KBytes that can be used for this qrV2Entry before a warning message and SNMP trap is produced. This object returns the most significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use qrV264KBytesSoftLimit instead.

qrV2LowKBytesSoftLimit.name: qrV2LowKBytesSoftLimit
qrV2LowKBytesSoftLimit.description: The limit of KBytes that can be used for this qrV2Entry before a warning message and SNMP trap is produced. This object returns the least significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use qrV264KBytesSoftLimit instead.

qrV2SoftFileQuotaUnlimited.name: qrV2SoftFileQuotaUnlimited
qrV2SoftFileQuotaUnlimited.description: This flag designates whether or not the file based soft quota limit for this qrV2Entry is unlimited. If false(1) then qrV2SoftFileLimit is valid, if true(2) qrV2SoftFileLimit is unused and will return 0.

qrV2SoftFileLimit.name: qrV2SoftFileLimit
qrV2SoftFileLimit.description: The limit of files that can be used for this qrV2Entry before a warning message and SNMP trap is produced. This will return 0 if qrV2SoftFileQuotaUnlimited is true.

qrV264KBytesUsed.name: qrV264KBytesUsed
qrV264KBytesUsed.description: The current number of KBytes used for this qrV2Entry. This object returns all of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

qrV264KBytesLimit.name: qrV264KBytesLimit
qrV264KBytesLimit.description: The limit of KBytes that can be used for this qrV2Entry. This object returns all of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This will return 0 if qrV2QuotaUnlimited is true.

qrV264KBytesThreshold.name: qrV264KBytesThreshold
qrV264KBytesThreshold.description: A number of KBytes that when used by this entry produces a warning message. This object returns the all of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This will return 0 if qrV2ThresholdUnlimited is true.

qrV264KBytesSoftLimit.name: qrV264KBytesSoftLimit
qrV264KBytesSoftLimit.description: The limit of KBytes that can be used for this qrV2Entry before a warning message and SNMP trap is produced. This object returns all of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

qrV2VolumeName.name: qrV2VolumeName
qrV2VolumeName.description: Indicates the name of the volume to which this quota belongs to.

qrV2Vserver.name: qrV2Vserver
qrV2Vserver.description: Indicates the vserver to which the volume belongs. Name from the cluster interfaces. Only applicable to cluster-mode volume.

filesysMaxfilesAvail.name: filesysMaxfilesAvail
filesysMaxfilesAvail.description: The count of the maximum number of files allowable on the root volume. This object is deprecated - use dfEntry.dfMaxFilesAvail instead.

filesysMaxfilesUsed.name: filesysMaxfilesUsed
filesysMaxfilesUsed.description: The count of the number of files currently in use on the root volume. This object is deprecated - use dfEntry.dfMaxFilesUsed instead.

filesysMaxfilesPossible.name: filesysMaxfilesPossible
filesysMaxfilesPossible.description: The largest value to which the filesysMaxfilesAvail parameter above can be increased by reconfiguration on the root volume. This object is deprecated - use dfEntry.dfMaxFilesPossible.

dfTable.name: dfTable
dfTable.description: Provide a report of the available disk space on the file systems. The tables shows the available disk space for volumes as well as aggregates. For node volumes and aggregates, only online volumes and aggregates are reported. For cluster volumes and aggregates, the dfStateOnline is set and the value for other fields are undefined when volumes and aggregates are not online.

dfEntry.name: dfEntry
dfEntry.description: Provide a report of the available disk space on the referenced file system. For entries returned from the cluster interfaces only, if the dfRowInfo is not set to 'available', the values reported for other fields may not be valid.

dfIndex.name: dfIndex
dfIndex.description: A number that identifies this entry for the referenced file system.

dfFileSys.name: dfFileSys
dfFileSys.description: The name for the referenced file system.

dfKBytesTotal.name: dfKBytesTotal
dfKBytesTotal.description: The total capacity in KBytes for the referenced file system.

dfKBytesUsed.name: dfKBytesUsed
dfKBytesUsed.description: The total disk space in KBytes that is in use on the referenced file system.

dfKBytesAvail.name: dfKBytesAvail
dfKBytesAvail.description: The total disk space in KBytes that is free for use on the referenced file system.

dfPerCentKBytesCapacity.name: dfPerCentKBytesCapacity
dfPerCentKBytesCapacity.description: The percentage of disk space currently in use on the referenced file system.

dfInodesUsed.name: dfInodesUsed
dfInodesUsed.description: The total number of inodes in use on the referenced file system.

dfInodesFree.name: dfInodesFree
dfInodesFree.description: The total number of inodes that are available for use on the referenced file system.

dfPerCentInodeCapacity.name: dfPerCentInodeCapacity
dfPerCentInodeCapacity.description: The percentage of disk space currently in use based on inode counts, on the referenced file system.

dfMountedOn.name: dfMountedOn
dfMountedOn.description: The name of the file on which this file system is mounted.

dfMaxFilesAvail.name: dfMaxFilesAvail
dfMaxFilesAvail.description: The count of the maximum number of files allowable on the referenced file system.

dfMaxFilesUsed.name: dfMaxFilesUsed
dfMaxFilesUsed.description: The count of the number of files currently in use on the referenced file system.

dfMaxFilesPossible.name: dfMaxFilesPossible
dfMaxFilesPossible.description: The largest value to which the filesysMaxfilesAvail parameter above can be increased by reconfiguration on the referenced file system.

dfHighTotalKBytes.name: dfHighTotalKBytes
dfHighTotalKBytes.description: The total capacity in KBytes for the referenced file system. This object returns the most significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use df64TotalKBytes instead.

dfLowTotalKBytes.name: dfLowTotalKBytes
dfLowTotalKBytes.description: The total capacity in KBytes for the referenced file system. This object returns the least significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use df64TotalKBytes instead.

dfHighUsedKBytes.name: dfHighUsedKBytes
dfHighUsedKBytes.description: The total disk space in KBytes that is in use on the referenced file system. This object returns the most significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use df64UsedKBytes instead.

dfLowUsedKBytes.name: dfLowUsedKBytes
dfLowUsedKBytes.description: The total disk space in KBytes that is in use on the referenced file system. This object returns the least significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use df64UsedKBytes instead.

dfHighAvailKBytes.name: dfHighAvailKBytes
dfHighAvailKBytes.description: The total disk space in KBytes that is free for use on the referenced file system. This object returns the most significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use df64AvailKBytes instead.

dfLowAvailKBytes.name: dfLowAvailKBytes
dfLowAvailKBytes.description: The total disk space in KBytes that is free for use on the referenced file system. This object returns the least significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use df64AvailKBytes instead.

dfStatus.name: dfStatus
dfStatus.description: The status of the file system.

dfMirrorStatus.name: dfMirrorStatus
dfMirrorStatus.description: Overall mirror status of the file system.

dfPlexCount.name: dfPlexCount
dfPlexCount.description: Number of plexes in this file system.

dfHighSisSharedKBytes.name: dfHighSisSharedKBytes
dfHighSisSharedKBytes.description: The total amount of data in KBytes that is shared by more than one instance on the referenced file system. This object returns the most significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use df64SisSharedKBytes instead.

dfLowSisSharedKBytes.name: dfLowSisSharedKBytes
dfLowSisSharedKBytes.description: The total amount of data in KBytes that is shared by more than one instance on the referenced file system. This object returns the least significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use df64SisSharedKBytes instead.

dfHighSisSavedKBytes.name: dfHighSisSavedKBytes
dfHighSisSavedKBytes.description: The total disk space in KBytes that is saved by storing only one copy of the duplicated blocks on the referenced file system. The object returns the most significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use df64SisSavedKBytes instead.

dfLowSisSavedKBytes.name: dfLowSisSavedKBytes
dfLowSisSavedKBytes.description: The total disk space in KBytes that is saved by storing only one copy of the duplicated blocks on the referenced file system. The object returns the least significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use df64SisSavedKBytes instead.

dfPerCentSaved.name: dfPerCentSaved
dfPerCentSaved.description: The percentage of disk space saved by eliminating the duplicated blocks on the referenced file system.

df64TotalKBytes.name: df64TotalKBytes
df64TotalKBytes.description: The total capacity in KBytes for the referenced file system. This object returns all of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

df64UsedKBytes.name: df64UsedKBytes
df64UsedKBytes.description: The total disk space in KBytes that is in use on the referenced file system. This object returns all of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

df64AvailKBytes.name: df64AvailKBytes
df64AvailKBytes.description: The total disk space in KBytes that is free for use on the referenced file system. This object returns all of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

df64SisSharedKBytes.name: df64SisSharedKBytes
df64SisSharedKBytes.description: The total amount of data in KBytes that is shared by more than one instance on the referenced file system. This object returns all of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

df64SisSavedKBytes.name: df64SisSavedKBytes
df64SisSavedKBytes.description: The total disk space in KBytes that is saved by storing only one copy of the duplicated blocks on the referenced file system. The object returns all of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

dfVserver.name: dfVserver
dfVserver.description: Name of the vserver to which the volume belongs. For aggregate and aggregate snapshot it will be an empty string. This field is returned only from the cluster interfaces.

dfStateOnline.name: dfStateOnline
dfStateOnline.description: The state of the cluster aggregates and volumes. If this is not true, all the values for the fields of this table are undefined. This field is returned only from the cluster interfaces.

dfRowInfo.name: dfRowInfo
dfRowInfo.description: Volume or aggregate and its snapshot is 'available' or 'partiallyAvailable'. This field is returned only from the cluster interfaces. Possible values for this field are: 'available' Indicates a normal case when everything went fine while fetching the values for the fields of this table and all values returned are valid. 'partiallyAvailable' Indicates something went wrong while fetching the values for the fields of this table and not all values are valid. For fields that could not be fetched, default values are set. For integers it is -1, for counters 0, and for string it is null.

df64CompressSaved.name: df64CompressSaved
df64CompressSaved.description: Provides the compression savings in a volume in KBytes. This is only returned for volumes.

dfCompressSavedPercent.name: dfCompressSavedPercent
dfCompressSavedPercent.description: Provides the percentage of compression savings in a volume, which is ((compr_saved/(compr_saved + used)) * 100). This is only returned for volumes.

df64DedupeSaved.name: df64DedupeSaved
df64DedupeSaved.description: Provides the deduplication savings in a volume in KBytes. This is only returned for volumes.

dfDedupeSavedPercent.name: dfDedupeSavedPercent
dfDedupeSavedPercent.description: Provides the percentage of deduplication savings in a volume, which is ((dedup_saved/(dedup_saved + used)) * 100). This is only returned for volumes.

df64TotalSaved.name: df64TotalSaved
df64TotalSaved.description: Provides the total savings due to deduplication & compression in a volume in KBytes. This is only returned for volumes.

dfTotalSavedPercent.name: dfTotalSavedPercent
dfTotalSavedPercent.description: Provides the percentage of total savings due to deduplication & compression in a volume, which is ((total_saved/(total_saved + used)) * 100). This is only returned for volumes.

df64TotalReservedKBytes.name: df64TotalReservedKBytes
df64TotalReservedKBytes.description: The total disk space in KBytes that is reserved on the referenced file system.

slTable.name: slTable
slTable.description: Provide a report of the snapshots on the root volume. This table is deprecated - use slVTable instead.

slEntry.name: slEntry
slEntry.description: Provide a report on a given snapshot on the root volume. This object is deprecated - use slVEntry instead.

slIndex.name: slIndex
slIndex.description: A number that identifies this entry for the referenced file system.

slMonth.name: slMonth
slMonth.description: The month in which the snapshot was created.

slDay.name: slDay
slDay.description: The day on which the snapshot was created.

slHour.name: slHour
slHour.description: The hour in which the snapshot was created.

slMinutes.name: slMinutes
slMinutes.description: The minute in which the snapshot was created.

slName.name: slName
slName.description: The name of the referenced snapshot.

slVTable.name: slVTable
slVTable.description: Provide a report of the snapshots on the file systems.

slVEntry.name: slVEntry
slVEntry.description: Provide a report on a given snapshot on the file system. Indices select the volume of the snapshot and the snapshot entry itself.

slVIndex.name: slVIndex
slVIndex.description: A number that identifies this entry for the referenced file system.

slVMonth.name: slVMonth
slVMonth.description: The month in which the snapshot was created.

slVDay.name: slVDay
slVDay.description: The day on which the snapshot was created.

slVHour.name: slVHour
slVHour.description: The hour in which the snapshot was created.

slVMinutes.name: slVMinutes
slVMinutes.description: The minute in which the snapshot was created.

slVName.name: slVName
slVName.description: The name of the referenced snapshot.

slVVolume.name: slVVolume
slVVolume.description: A number that identifies the volume / aggregate that contains this snapshot.

slVNumber.name: slVNumber
slVNumber.description: Number of snapshots for this volume / aggregate.

slVVolumeName.name: slVVolumeName
slVVolumeName.description: The name of the volume / aggregate. This does not have a /vol/ prefix.

slVType.name: slVType
slVType.description: Indicates the type of container for this snapshot.

slQTable.name: slQTable
slQTable.description: Provide a report of the snapshots and their contents on the file systems.

slQEntry.name: slQEntry
slQEntry.description: Provide a report on a given snapshot for a given qtree on the file system. Indices select the volume and qtree of the snapshot and the snapshot entry itself.

slQIndex.name: slQIndex
slQIndex.description: A number that identifies this entry for the referenced file system.

slQVolume.name: slQVolume
slQVolume.description: A number that identifies the volume that contains this snapshot.

slQQtree.name: slQQtree
slQQtree.description: A number that identifies the qtree that contains this snapshot.

slQSnapshotName.name: slQSnapshotName
slQSnapshotName.description: The name of the referenced snapshot.

slQSnapshotTime.name: slQSnapshotTime
slQSnapshotTime.description: Time of the snapshot on the system. The time in seconds since January 1, 1970.

slQQtreeName.name: slQQtreeName
slQQtreeName.description: A string that indicates which qtree is in this snapshot

slQQtreeContent.name: slQQtreeContent
slQQtreeContent.description: The content of the qtree tree

slQSource.name: slQSource
slQSource.description: The source of this qtree for a replicated qtree. '-' for an original qtree.

slQSourceTime.name: slQSourceTime
slQSourceTime.description: Time of the source snapshot for a replicated qtree. Time of the current snapshot for an original qtree. The time in seconds since January 1, 1970. 0 if the qtree is in a transitioning stage

slQVolumeName.name: slQVolumeName
slQVolumeName.description: The name of the volume. This does not have a /vol/ prefix.

dfNumber.name: dfNumber
dfNumber.description: Number of entries in the dfTable table.

fsOverallStatus.name: fsOverallStatus
fsOverallStatus.description: An indication of overall file system health. 'ok' indicates that all file systems have adequate space. 'nearlyFull' means that one or more is nearly full (more than 95% full). 'full' means that one or more are more than 98% full.

fsStatusMessage.name: fsStatusMessage
fsStatusMessage.description: A string indicating any file systems which are full or nearly full.

fsMaxUsedBytesPerCent.name: fsMaxUsedBytesPerCent
fsMaxUsedBytesPerCent.description: The percentage of space currently in use or reserved by the fullest file system.

fsMaxUsedInodesPerCent.name: fsMaxUsedInodesPerCent
fsMaxUsedInodesPerCent.description: The percentage of inodes currently in use by the fullest file system.

volTable.name: volTable
volTable.description: List the volumes defined on the system, including offline volumes.

volEntry.name: volEntry
volEntry.description: Provide details about a particular volume. For entries returned only from the cluster interfaces, if the volRowInfo is not set to 'available', the values reported by other fields of this table may not be valid.

volIndex.name: volIndex
volIndex.description: A number that identifies this volume. The volIndex is not related to any other table defined in this MIB, and may change as volumes are created and destroyed.

volName.name: volName
volName.description: Name of the volume. This includes no /vol/ prefix.

volOwningHost.name: volOwningHost
volOwningHost.description: Indication of which host owns this volume. This field is not supported in a cluster.

volState.name: volState
volState.description: State of the volume, such as 'online' or 'offline'.

volStatus.name: volStatus
volStatus.description: Status of the volume, such as 'normal' or 'reconstructing'. May include several values separated by comma and space.

volOptions.name: volOptions
volOptions.description: Options associated with the volume, such as 'root' and 'nosnapdir=off'. May include several values separated by comma.

volUUID.name: volUUID
volUUID.description: A unique id associated with the volume.

volAggrName.name: volAggrName
volAggrName.description: Name of the aggregate this flexible volume is a part of.

volType.name: volType
volType.description: Type of this volume, older volumes are traditional while newer volumes contained in aggregates are flexible.

volClone.name: volClone
volClone.description: True indicates flexible volume is a clone.

volCloneOf.name: volCloneOf
volCloneOf.description: Name of flexible volume this flexible volume is a clone of.

volVserver.name: volVserver
volVserver.description: Vserver to which the volume belongs. Name from the cluster interfaces. Only applicable to cluster-mode volume.

volMSID.name: volMSID
volMSID.description: The volume's Mirror Set ID. MSIDs are formatted as 10-character strings composed of 8 hex characters prefixed with '0x'. Only applicable to cluster-mode volume.

volDSID.name: volDSID
volDSID.description: The volume's Data Set ID. DSIDs are formatted as 10-character strings composed of 8 hex characters prefixed with '0x'. Only applicable to cluster-mode volume.

volSpaceGuaranteeEnabled.name: volSpaceGuaranteeEnabled
volSpaceGuaranteeEnabled.description: Whether or not the space guarantee style associated with the volume is currently in effect. This field does not appear if the flexible volume is restricted or offline.

volSpaceGuarantee.name: volSpaceGuarantee
volSpaceGuarantee.description: The space guarantee style associated with the volume, such as 'volume', etc. This field does not appear if the flexible volume is restricted or offline.

volLanguage.name: volLanguage
volLanguage.description: The language currently set for the volume. For example, 'English '.

volLanguageCode.name: volLanguageCode
volLanguageCode.description: The language code currently set for the volume. For example, 'en'.

volCloneChildrenList.name: volCloneChildrenList
volCloneChildrenList.description: A comma separated list of all volume's child clones.

volJunctionPathActive.name: volJunctionPathActive
volJunctionPathActive.description: Indicates if a Junction Path is active on this volume. This field is returned only from the cluster interfaces.

volJunctionPath.name: volJunctionPath
volJunctionPath.description: The mount path for the volume, relative to the root volume. This field is returned only from the cluster interfaces.

volJunctionPathSource.name: volJunctionPathSource
volJunctionPathSource.description: Source directory of the Junction Path for this volume. This field is returned only from the cluster interfaces. Two possible values are 'LSM volume' for Load Share Mirror volumes 'RW volume' for Read-Write volumes.

volRowInfo.name: volRowInfo
volRowInfo.description: Volume is 'available' or 'partiallyAvailable'. This field is returned only from the cluster interfaces. Two possible values are: 'available' Indicates a normal case when everything went fine while fetching the values for the fields of this table and all values returned are valid. 'partiallyAvailable' Indicates something went wrong while fetching the values of the fields for this table and not all values are valid. For fields that could not be fetched, default values are set. For integers it is -1, for counters 0, and for string it is null.

volNvfail.name: volNvfail
volNvfail.description: Indicates whether nvfail option is enabled on this volume.

volInNvfailedState.name: volInNvfailedState
volInNvfailedState.description: Indicates whether the volume is in nvfailed state. This is only applicable to cluster-mode volumes.

volInstanceUUID.name: volInstanceUUID
volInstanceUUID.description: A unique id associated with the volume that moves with the volume when the volume is migrated.

volProvenanceUUID.name: volProvenanceUUID
volProvenanceUUID.description: A unique id associated with the volume that identifies the source of the volume content.

volDrForceNvfail.name: volDrForceNvfail
volDrForceNvfail.description: Indicates whether dr-force-nvfail option is enabled on this volume. If true, volume would be put in a special state called 'in-nvfailed-state' by switchover operation. The protocol access on the volume in 'in-nvfailed-state' is blocked. This will cause the client applications to crash and thus prevent access to data on the volume. To get out of this situation, admin needs to manually clear the 'in-nvfailed-state' on the volume. By default, dr-force-nvfail option value is false.

volNumber.name: volNumber
volNumber.description: Number of volumes in the volTable.

qtreeTable.name: qtreeTable
qtreeTable.description: Provide a list of the qtrees on the system.

qtreeEntry.name: qtreeEntry
qtreeEntry.description: Provide details about a particular qtree.

qtreeVolume.name: qtreeVolume
qtreeVolume.description: A number that identifies the volume that contains this qtree.

qtreeVolumeName.name: qtreeVolumeName
qtreeVolumeName.description: The name of the volume that contains this qtree. This includes no /vol/prefix.

qtreeId.name: qtreeId
qtreeId.description: The Id number of the qtree.

qtreeStyle.name: qtreeStyle
qtreeStyle.description: The security style of the qtree.

qtreeOplock.name: qtreeOplock
qtreeOplock.description: An indication of whether the oplocks is enabled or not for this qtree.

qtreeVserver.name: qtreeVserver
qtreeVserver.description: Indicates the vserver to which the volume belongs. Name from the cluster interfaces. Only applicable to cluster-mode volume.

qtreeExportPolicy.name: qtreeExportPolicy
qtreeExportPolicy.description: Indicates the export policy assigned to the qtree.

qtreeIsExportPolicyInherited.name: qtreeIsExportPolicyInherited
qtreeIsExportPolicyInherited.description: Indicates the export policy assigned to the qtree is inherited from the parent volume.

qtreeMode.name: qtreeMode
qtreeMode.description: The file permission bits of the qtree.

aggrTable.name: aggrTable
aggrTable.description: List the aggregates defined on the system, including offline aggregates.

aggrEntry.name: aggrEntry
aggrEntry.description: Provide details about a particular aggregate. For entries returned only from the cluster interfaces, if the aggrRowInfo is not set to 'available', the values reported by other fields of this table may not be valid.

aggrIndex.name: aggrIndex
aggrIndex.description: A number that identifies this aggregate. The aggrIndex is not related to any other table defined in this MIB, and may change as aggregates are created and destroyed.

aggrName.name: aggrName
aggrName.description: Name of the aggregate. This includes no /vol/ prefix.

aggrOwningHost.name: aggrOwningHost
aggrOwningHost.description: Indication of which host owns this aggregate. This field is not supported in a cluster.

aggrState.name: aggrState
aggrState.description: State of the aggregate, such as 'online' or 'offline'.

aggrStatus.name: aggrStatus
aggrStatus.description: Status of the aggregate, such as 'normal' or 'reconstructing'. May include several values separated by comma and space.

aggrUUID.name: aggrUUID
aggrUUID.description: A unique id associated with the aggregate.

aggrFlexvollist.name: aggrFlexvollist
aggrFlexvollist.description: List of all the flexible volumes within this aggregate. This field is not supported in a cluster.

aggrType.name: aggrType
aggrType.description: Type of this container, containers containing flexible volumes are aggregate.

aggrRaidType.name: aggrRaidType
aggrRaidType.description: Type of raid protection of the aggregate, such as 'raid0', 'mirrored raid0', 'raid4', 'mirrored raid4', 'raid_dp', 'mirrored raid_dp'.

aggrHAType.name: aggrHAType
aggrHAType.description: Aggregate failover type, such as 'cfo' for cluster failover, 'sfo' for storage failover. This is set to 'none' if aggregate failover type is not known.

aggrOwners.name: aggrOwners
aggrOwners.description: Current owner(s) or the node(s) to which the aggregate belongs to. In case of striped aggregates, this will be a comma separated list of nodes to which the aggregate belongs to.

aggrRowInfo.name: aggrRowInfo
aggrRowInfo.description: Aggregate is 'available' or 'partiallyAvailable'. This OID is available only from the cluster management interfaces. Two possible values are: 'available' : Indicates a normal case when everything went fine while fetching the values of the fields for this table and all values returned are valid. 'partiallyAvailable' : Indicates something went wrong while fetching the values of the fields for this table and not all the values are valid. For fields that could not be fetched, default values are set. For integers it is -1, for counters 0, and for string it is null.

aggrVolumeFootprints.name: aggrVolumeFootprints
aggrVolumeFootprints.description: Footprint of data and metadata inside volumes belonging to the Aggregate. This field is deprecated in Data ONTAP 8.3 and later - use the volume-footprints field of the aggr-space-get-iter ZAPI instead.

aggrVolumeFootprintsPercent.name: aggrVolumeFootprintsPercent
aggrVolumeFootprintsPercent.description: Footprint of data and metadata inside volumes belonging to the aggregate as a percentage of aggregate size. This field is deprecated in Data ONTAP 8.3 and later - use the volume-footprints-percent field of the aggr-space-get-iter ZAPI instead.

aggrFilesystemMetadata.name: aggrFilesystemMetadata
aggrFilesystemMetadata.description: Metadata of the Aggregate. This field is deprecated in Data ONTAP 8.3 and later - use the aggregate-metadata field of the aggr-space-get-iter ZAPI instead.

aggrFilesystemMetadataPercent.name: aggrFilesystemMetadataPercent
aggrFilesystemMetadataPercent.description: Metadata of the Aggregate as a percentage of Aggregate size. This field is deprecated in Data ONTAP 8.3 and later - use the aggregate-metadata-percent field of the aggr-space-get-iter ZAPI instead.

aggrNumber.name: aggrNumber
aggrNumber.description: Number of aggregates in the aggrTable.

volMoveStatusEntry.name: volMoveStatusEntry
volMoveStatusEntry.description: Provide movement details of a particular volume

volMoveIndex.name: volMoveIndex
volMoveIndex.description: A number that identifies this volume. The volIndex is not related to any other table defined in this MIB, and may change as volumes are created and destroyed.

volMoveSrcName.name: volMoveSrcName
volMoveSrcName.description: Name of the vol move source volume. This will not have the /vol/ prefix.

volMoveDstaggrName.name: volMoveDstaggrName
volMoveDstaggrName.description: Name of the vol move destination aggregate

volMoveCOattempts.name: volMoveCOattempts
volMoveCOattempts.description: Maximum Cutover attempts for specified vol move operation

volMoveCOtime.name: volMoveCOtime
volMoveCOtime.description: Maximum Cutover time for specified vol move operation

volMoveState.name: volMoveState
volMoveState.description: State of the vol move operation

raidTable.name: raidTable
raidTable.description: Display RAID configuration information for the root volume. This table is deprecated - use raidVTable instead.

raidEntry.name: raidEntry
raidEntry.description: Display RAID configuration information for the referenced disk drive. This only works for disks contained within the root volume, and will include spare drives. This object is deprecated - use raidVEntry instead.

raidIndex.name: raidIndex
raidIndex.description: A number that identifies this entry for the referenced disk drive.

raidDiskName.name: raidDiskName
raidDiskName.description: The name identifying the referenced disk drive.

raidStatus.name: raidStatus
raidStatus.description: The status of the referenced disk drive.

raidDiskId.name: raidDiskId
raidDiskId.description: The disk identifier for the referenced disk drive.

raidScsiAdapter.name: raidScsiAdapter
raidScsiAdapter.description: The identifier of the SCSI adapter for the referenced disk drive.

raidScsiId.name: raidScsiId
raidScsiId.description: The identifier for the referenced disk drive on the referenced SCSI adapter.

raidUsedMb.name: raidUsedMb
raidUsedMb.description: The number of MBytes currently in use on the referenced disk drive.

raidUsedBlocks.name: raidUsedBlocks
raidUsedBlocks.description: The number of Blocks currently in use on the referenced disk drive.

raidTotalMb.name: raidTotalMb
raidTotalMb.description: The number of MBytes physically available on the referenced disk drive.

raidTotalBlocks.name: raidTotalBlocks
raidTotalBlocks.description: The number of Blocks physically available on the referenced disk drive.

raidCompletionPerCent.name: raidCompletionPerCent
raidCompletionPerCent.description: In the case when reconstruction/adding a spare, verification or scrubbing is in progress, the percent of such reconstruction, verification or scrubbing that has been completed on the referenced disk drive.

raidVEntry.name: raidVEntry
raidVEntry.description: Display RAID configuration information for the referenced aggregate, raid group, and disk drive.

raidVIndex.name: raidVIndex
raidVIndex.description: A number that identifies this disk drive within the given aggregate and RAID group.

raidVDiskName.name: raidVDiskName
raidVDiskName.description: The name identifying the referenced disk drive.

raidVStatus.name: raidVStatus
raidVStatus.description: The status of the referenced disk drive.

raidVDiskId.name: raidVDiskId
raidVDiskId.description: The disk identifier for the referenced disk drive. This OID is not available from the Cluster management interfaces. This object is deprecated.

raidVScsiAdapter.name: raidVScsiAdapter
raidVScsiAdapter.description: The identifier of the SCSI adapter for the referenced disk drive. This OID is not available from the Cluster management interfaces. This object is deprecated.

raidVScsiId.name: raidVScsiId
raidVScsiId.description: The identifier for the referenced disk drive on the referenced SCSI adapter. This OID is not available from the Cluster management interfaces. This object is deprecated.

raidVUsedMb.name: raidVUsedMb
raidVUsedMb.description: The number of MBytes currently in use on the referenced disk drive.

raidVUsedBlocks.name: raidVUsedBlocks
raidVUsedBlocks.description: The number of Blocks currently in use on the referenced disk drive. This object is deprecated. Use raidV64UsedBlocks object instead.

raidVTotalMb.name: raidVTotalMb
raidVTotalMb.description: The number of MBytes physically available on the referenced disk drive.

raidVTotalBlocks.name: raidVTotalBlocks
raidVTotalBlocks.description: The number of Blocks physically available on the referenced disk drive. This object is deprecated. Use raidV64TotalBlocks object instead.

raidVCompletionPerCent.name: raidVCompletionPerCent
raidVCompletionPerCent.description: In the case when rapid raid recovery, disk copy, reconstruction/adding a spare, verification or scrubbing is in progress, the percent of such copy, reconstruction, verification or scrubbing that has been completed on the referenced disk drive.

raidVVol.name: raidVVol
raidVVol.description: A number that identifies the aggregate that this entry belongs to. The first aggregate is '1'.

raidVGroup.name: raidVGroup
raidVGroup.description: A number that identifies the RAID group within the given aggregate that this entry belongs to. The first RAID group is '1', and number across all plexes.

raidVDiskNumber.name: raidVDiskNumber
raidVDiskNumber.description: The number of disks within this RAID group.

raidVGroupNumber.name: raidVGroupNumber
raidVGroupNumber.description: The number of RAID groups within this aggregate.

raidVDiskPort.name: raidVDiskPort
raidVDiskPort.description: A number that indicates which port of the disk is being used by the primary path to the disk. For a dual-ported disk, values of portA and portB indicate which port is being used. If the disk only has a single port, the value is portSingle, and if the port is not active, the value is portNone. This OID is not available from the Cluster management interfaces. This object is deprecated.

raidVSecondaryDiskName.name: raidVSecondaryDiskName
raidVSecondaryDiskName.description: The name identifying the secondary path to the referenced disk drive. This OID is not available from the Cluster management interfaces. This object is deprecated.

raidVSecondaryDiskPort.name: raidVSecondaryDiskPort
raidVSecondaryDiskPort.description: A number that indicates which port of the disk is being used by the secondary path to the disk. For a dual-ported disk, values of portA and portB indicate which port is being used. If the disk only has a single port, the value is portSingle, and if the port is not active, the value is portNone. This OID is not available from the Cluster management interfaces. This object is deprecated.

raidVShelf.name: raidVShelf
raidVShelf.description: Number identifying the shelf where the disk is located.

raidVBay.name: raidVBay
raidVBay.description: Number identifying the disk bay within the shelf where the disk is located.

raidVPlex.name: raidVPlex
raidVPlex.description: A number that identifies the plex within the given aggregate that this entry belongs to. The first plex is '1'.

raidVPlexGroup.name: raidVPlexGroup
raidVPlexGroup.description: A number that identifies the RAID group within the given plex that this entry belongs to. The first RAID group is '1'.

raidVPlexNumber.name: raidVPlexNumber
raidVPlexNumber.description: The number of plexes within this aggregate. This number is always 1 or 2.

raidVPlexName.name: raidVPlexName
raidVPlexName.description: A name that identifies the plex that this entry belongs to. A plex name can be anything, but is usually a string like 'plex0' or 'plex1'.

raidVSectorSize.name: raidVSectorSize
raidVSectorSize.description: A number that specifies bytes per sector for this entry. Values are '512' or '520'.

raidVDiskSerialNumber.name: raidVDiskSerialNumber
raidVDiskSerialNumber.description: Serial number of the referenced disk drive.

raidVDiskVendor.name: raidVDiskVendor
raidVDiskVendor.description: The vendor of the referenced disk drive.

raidVDiskModel.name: raidVDiskModel
raidVDiskModel.description: Model string of the referenced disk drive.

raidVDiskFirmwareRevision.name: raidVDiskFirmwareRevision
raidVDiskFirmwareRevision.description: Firmware revision number of the referenced disk drive.

raidVDiskRPM.name: raidVDiskRPM
raidVDiskRPM.description: RPM of the referenced disk drive.

raidVDiskType.name: raidVDiskType
raidVDiskType.description: Interface type of the referenced disk drive. e.g SCSI, or ATA.

raidVDiskPool.name: raidVDiskPool
raidVDiskPool.description: A name that identifies the disk pool that this entry belongs to.

raidVDiskCopyDestDiskName.name: raidVDiskCopyDestDiskName
raidVDiskCopyDestDiskName.description: When raidVStatus value is prefailed, this string identifies the name of the disk which is the copy target of the referenced prefailed disk.

raidVDiskUID.name: raidVDiskUID
raidVDiskUID.description: Unique identifier for the disk. The maximum length is 90 characters.

raidV64UsedBlocks.name: raidV64UsedBlocks
raidV64UsedBlocks.description: The number of Blocks currently in use on the referenced disk drive. This object returns all of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

raidV64TotalBlocks.name: raidV64TotalBlocks
raidV64TotalBlocks.description: The number of Blocks physically available on the referenced disk drive. This object returns all of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

raidVCarrierID.name: raidVCarrierID
raidVCarrierID.description: Unique identifier of the disk carrier.

spareEntry.name: spareEntry
spareEntry.description: Display configuration information for the referenced spare disk drive.

spareIndex.name: spareIndex
spareIndex.description: A number that identifies this entry for the referenced disk drive in the list of spare disk drives.

spareDiskName.name: spareDiskName
spareDiskName.description: The name identifying the referenced spare disk drive.

spareStatus.name: spareStatus
spareStatus.description: The status of the referenced spare disk drive.

spareDiskId.name: spareDiskId
spareDiskId.description: The disk identifier for the referenced spare disk drive. This OID is not available from the Cluster management interfaces. This object is deprecated.

spareScsiAdapter.name: spareScsiAdapter
spareScsiAdapter.description: The identifier of the SCSI adapter for the referenced spare disk drive. This OID is not available from the Cluster management interfaces. This object is deprecated.

spareScsiId.name: spareScsiId
spareScsiId.description: The identifier for the referenced spare disk drive on the referenced SCSI adapter. This OID is not available from the Cluster management interfaces. This object is deprecated.

spareTotalMb.name: spareTotalMb
spareTotalMb.description: The number of MBytes physically available on the referenced spare disk drive.

spareTotalBlocks.name: spareTotalBlocks
spareTotalBlocks.description: The number of Blocks physically available on the referenced spare disk drive. This object is deprecated. Use spare64TotalBlocks object instead.

spareDiskPort.name: spareDiskPort
spareDiskPort.description: A number that indicates which port of the disk is being used by the primary path to the disk. For a dual-ported disk, values of portA and portB indicate which port is being used. If the disk only has a single port, the value is portSingle, and if the port is not active, the value is portNone. This OID is not available from the Cluster management interfaces. This object is deprecated.

spareSecondaryDiskName.name: spareSecondaryDiskName
spareSecondaryDiskName.description: The name identifying the secondary path to the referenced disk drive. This OID is not available from the Cluster management interfaces. This object is deprecated.

spareSecondaryDiskPort.name: spareSecondaryDiskPort
spareSecondaryDiskPort.description: A number that indicates which port of the disk is being used by the secondary path to the disk. For a dual-ported disk, values of portA and portB indicate which port is being used. If the disk only has a single port, the value is portSingle, and if the port is not active, the value is portNone. This OID is not available from the Cluster management interfaces. This object is deprecated.

spareShelf.name: spareShelf
spareShelf.description: Number identifying the shelf where the disk is located.

spareBay.name: spareBay
spareBay.description: Number identifying the disk bay within the shelf where the disk is located.

sparePool.name: sparePool
sparePool.description: A name that identifies the disk pool that this entry belongs to.

spareSectorSize.name: spareSectorSize
spareSectorSize.description: A number that specifies bytes per sector for this entry. Values are '512' or '520'.

spareDiskSerialNumber.name: spareDiskSerialNumber
spareDiskSerialNumber.description: Serial number of the referenced disk drive.

spareDiskVendor.name: spareDiskVendor
spareDiskVendor.description: The vendor of the referenced disk drive.

spareDiskModel.name: spareDiskModel
spareDiskModel.description: Model string of the referenced disk drive.

spareDiskFirmwareRevision.name: spareDiskFirmwareRevision
spareDiskFirmwareRevision.description: Firmware revision number of the referenced disk drive.

spareDiskRPM.name: spareDiskRPM
spareDiskRPM.description: RPM of the referenced disk drive.

spareDiskType.name: spareDiskType
spareDiskType.description: Interface type of the referenced disk drive. e.g SCSI, or ATA.

spareDiskUID.name: spareDiskUID
spareDiskUID.description: External unique identifier for the disk. The Maximum length is 90 characters.

spare64TotalBlocks.name: spare64TotalBlocks
spare64TotalBlocks.description: The number of Blocks physically available on the referenced spare disk drive. This object returns all of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

spareCarrierID.name: spareCarrierID
spareCarrierID.description: Unique identifier of the disk carrier.

diskTotalCount.name: diskTotalCount
diskTotalCount.description: The total number of disks on the system.

diskActiveCount.name: diskActiveCount
diskActiveCount.description: The number of disks which are currently active, including parity disks.

diskReconstructingCount.name: diskReconstructingCount
diskReconstructingCount.description: The number of disks which are currently being reconstructed.

diskReconstructingParityCount.name: diskReconstructingParityCount
diskReconstructingParityCount.description: The number of parity disks which are currently being reconstructed.

diskVerifyingParityCount.name: diskVerifyingParityCount
diskVerifyingParityCount.description: The number of disks which are currently being verified.

diskScrubbingCount.name: diskScrubbingCount
diskScrubbingCount.description: The number of disks which are currently being scrubbed.

diskFailedCount.name: diskFailedCount
diskFailedCount.description: The number of disks which are currently broken.

diskSpareCount.name: diskSpareCount
diskSpareCount.description: The number of available spare disks.

diskAddingSpareCount.name: diskAddingSpareCount
diskAddingSpareCount.description: The number of spare disks which are currently being added into a RAID group.

diskFailedMessage.name: diskFailedMessage
diskFailedMessage.description: If diskFailedCount is non-zero, this is a string describing the failed disk or disks. Each failed disk is described with a sentence like Disk on adapter 8a, shelf 1, bay 0, failed. or Disk on stack 3, shelf 2, bay 2, failed.

diskPrefailedCount.name: diskPrefailedCount
diskPrefailedCount.description: The number of disks which are prefailed and marked for rapid raid recovery.

raidVNumber.name: raidVNumber
raidVNumber.description: Number of entries in the raidVTable table. This is the total number of aggregates in the system.

spareNumber.name: spareNumber
spareNumber.description: Number of entries in the spareTable table.

otherDiskNumber.name: otherDiskNumber
otherDiskNumber.description: Number of entries in the otherDiskTable table.

raidPNumber.name: raidPNumber
raidPNumber.description: Number of entries in the raidPTable table. This is the total number of aggregates in the system.

otherDiskEntry.name: otherDiskEntry
otherDiskEntry.description: Display configuration information for the referenced disk drive.

otherDiskIndex.name: otherDiskIndex
otherDiskIndex.description: A number that identifies this entry for the referenced disk drive in the list of out-of-service disk drives. Out-of-service disks include all disks that are not in service in a raid group or available as a spare disk.

otherDiskDiskName.name: otherDiskDiskName
otherDiskDiskName.description: The name identifying the referenced disk drive.

otherDiskStatus.name: otherDiskStatus
otherDiskStatus.description: The status of the referenced disk drive.

otherDiskDiskId.name: otherDiskDiskId
otherDiskDiskId.description: The disk identifier for the referenced disk drive. This OID is not available from the Cluster management interfaces. This object is deprecated.

otherDiskScsiAdapter.name: otherDiskScsiAdapter
otherDiskScsiAdapter.description: The identifier of the SCSI adapter for the referenced disk drive. This OID is not available from the Cluster management interfaces. This object is deprecated.

otherDiskScsiId.name: otherDiskScsiId
otherDiskScsiId.description: The identifier for the referenced disk drive on the referenced SCSI adapter. This OID is not available from the Cluster management interfaces. This object is deprecated.

otherDiskTotalMb.name: otherDiskTotalMb
otherDiskTotalMb.description: The number of MBytes physically available on the referenced disk drive.

otherDiskTotalBlocks.name: otherDiskTotalBlocks
otherDiskTotalBlocks.description: The number of Blocks physically available on the referenced disk drive. This object is deprecated. Use otherDisk64TotalBlocks object instead.

otherDiskDiskPort.name: otherDiskDiskPort
otherDiskDiskPort.description: A number that indicates which port of the disk is being used by the primary path to the disk. For a dual-ported disk, values of portA and portB indicate which port is being used. If the disk only has a single port, the value is portSingle, and if the port is not active, the value is portNone. This OID is not available from the Cluster management interfaces. This object is deprecated.

otherDiskSecondaryDiskName.name: otherDiskSecondaryDiskName
otherDiskSecondaryDiskName.description: The name identifying the secondary path to the referenced disk drive. This OID is not available from the Cluster management interfaces. This object is deprecated.

otherDiskSecondaryDiskPort.name: otherDiskSecondaryDiskPort
otherDiskSecondaryDiskPort.description: A number that indicates which port of the disk is being used by the secondary path to the disk. For a dual-ported disk, values of portA and portB indicate which port is being used. If the disk only has a single port, the value is portSingle, and if the port is not active, the value is portNone. This OID is not available from the Cluster management interfaces. This object is deprecated.

otherDiskShelf.name: otherDiskShelf
otherDiskShelf.description: Number identifying the shelf where the disk is located.

otherDiskBay.name: otherDiskBay
otherDiskBay.description: Number identifying the disk bay within the shelf where the disk is located.

otherDiskPool.name: otherDiskPool
otherDiskPool.description: A name that identifies the disk pool that this entry belongs to.

otherDiskSectorSize.name: otherDiskSectorSize
otherDiskSectorSize.description: A number that specifies bytes per sector for this entry. Values are '512' or '520'.

otherDiskSerialNumber.name: otherDiskSerialNumber
otherDiskSerialNumber.description: Serial number of the referenced disk drive.

otherDiskVendor.name: otherDiskVendor
otherDiskVendor.description: The vendor of the referenced disk drive.

otherDiskModel.name: otherDiskModel
otherDiskModel.description: Model string of the referenced disk drive.

otherDiskFirmwareRevision.name: otherDiskFirmwareRevision
otherDiskFirmwareRevision.description: Firmware revision number of the referenced disk drive.

otherDiskRPM.name: otherDiskRPM
otherDiskRPM.description: RPM of the referenced disk drive.

otherDiskType.name: otherDiskType
otherDiskType.description: Interface type of the referenced disk drive. e.g SCSI, or ATA.

otherDisk64TotalBlocks.name: otherDisk64TotalBlocks
otherDisk64TotalBlocks.description: The number of Blocks physically available on the referenced disk drive. This object returns all of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

otherDiskCarrierID.name: otherDiskCarrierID
otherDiskCarrierID.description: Unique identifier of the disk carrier.

raidPEntry.name: raidPEntry
raidPEntry.description: Display RAID configuration information for the referenced aggregate, plex, raid group, and disk drive.

raidPIndex.name: raidPIndex
raidPIndex.description: A number that identifies this disk drive within the given aggregate and RAID group.

raidPStatus.name: raidPStatus
raidPStatus.description: The status of the referenced disk drive.

raidPVol.name: raidPVol
raidPVol.description: A number that identifies the aggregate that this entry belongs to. The first aggregate is '1'.

raidPPlex.name: raidPPlex
raidPPlex.description: A number that identifies the plex that this entry belongs to. The first plex is '1'.

raidPGroup.name: raidPGroup
raidPGroup.description: A number that identifies the RAID group within the given plex that this entry belongs to. The first RAID group is '1'.

raidPPlexNumber.name: raidPPlexNumber
raidPPlexNumber.description: The number of plexes within this aggregate. This number is always 1 or 2.

raidPGroupNumber.name: raidPGroupNumber
raidPGroupNumber.description: The number of RAID groups within this plex.

raidPDiskNumber.name: raidPDiskNumber
raidPDiskNumber.description: The number of disks within this RAID group.

raidPPlexName.name: raidPPlexName
raidPPlexName.description: A name that identifies the plex that this entry belongs to. A plex name can be anything, but is usually a string like 'plex0' or 'plex1'.

raidPDiskName.name: raidPDiskName
raidPDiskName.description: The name identifying the referenced disk drive.

raidPDiskPort.name: raidPDiskPort
raidPDiskPort.description: A number that indicates which port of the disk is being used by the primary path to the disk. For a dual-ported disk, values of portA and portB indicate which port is being used. If the disk only has a single port, the value is portSingle, and if the port is not active, the value is portNone. cifsIsEnabled.name: cifsIsEnabled
cifsIsEnabled.description: Whether the CIFS protocol is active on the filer.

cifsIsLoginEnabled.description: Whether new CIFS connections to the filer are currently allowed.

cifsHostName.description: The host name used by the CIFS protocol on this filer.

cifsAltNames.name: cifsAltNames
cifsAltNames.description: Alternate names recognized by the filer.

cifsDomainJoined.name: cifsDomainJoined
cifsDomainJoined.description: Has the filer joined an NT domain? If this value is true, cifsDomainName will contain the name of the domain. Otherwise, the filer may have joined a WorkGroup, and cifsWGName will contain the name of the WorkGroup.

cifsDomainName.name: cifsDomainName
cifsDomainName.description: The domain name used by the CIFS protocol on this filer.

cifsWGName.name: cifsWGName
cifsWGName.description: The workgroup name (if any) used by the CIFS protocol on this filer.

cifsDCName.name: cifsDCName
cifsDCName.description: The name of the Domain Controller used by this filer to authenticate users and file requests.

cifsIsWinsEnabled.name: cifsIsWinsEnabled
cifsIsWinsEnabled.description: True if WINS name resolution is enabled on the filer.

cifsWinsServers.name: cifsWinsServers
cifsWinsServers.description: The name(s) of the WINS servers registered with the filer.

cifsSecurityModel.name: cifsSecurityModel
cifsSecurityModel.description: Which type of authentication semantics (Unix or PC) are in use for PC access to Unix files on the filer. If Unix semantics are in use, no ACL on a Unix file is ever checked. If PC semantics are in use, the share level ACL on the share containing the file is used for authentication instead of the group portion of the permissions on the file.

cifsPCGenericUser.name: cifsPCGenericUser
cifsPCGenericUser.description: The name of the generic PC user, if any. This username is used for CIFS access by Unix users who have not authenticated through CIFS or NT.

cifsOplocksEnabled.name: cifsOplocksEnabled
cifsOplocksEnabled.description: Whether oplocks are enabled on the filer.

cifsLevel2OplocksEnabled.name: cifsLevel2OplocksEnabled
cifsLevel2OplocksEnabled.description: Whether level 2 oplocks are enabled on the filer.

cifsPreserveCase.name: cifsPreserveCase
cifsPreserveCase.description: If this option is set to preserve-case (the default), all filename references will be case preserving. Otherwise, they are forced to lowercase.

cifsSymlinksEnabled.name: cifsSymlinksEnabled
cifsSymlinksEnabled.description: If this option is enabled, CIFS accesses will follow symbolic links using Unix semantics.

cifsSymlinkCycleProtEnabled.name: cifsSymlinkCycleProtEnabled
cifsSymlinkCycleProtEnabled.description: If this option is enabled, CIFS accesses will through symbolic links will check for cycles in the link graph.

ncAdminPort.name: ncAdminPort
ncAdminPort.description: Netcache Admin Port number - this is the first in the list of admin ports configured for the NetCache.

amNumber.name: amNumber
amNumber.description: The number of entries in the acceleration monitor table.

amMonitor.name: amMonitor
amMonitor.description: Variable for user defined SNMP traps to monitor whether there has been a status change of any of the acceleration servers that netcache is probing.

amMonitorString.name: amMonitorString
amMonitorString.description: Used in conjunction with amMonitor. This returns a string in format of: 'IP:port status' which reports the status of all the servers netcache is accelerating as of last status change.

amTable.name: amTable
amTable.description: A list of acceleration server and port entries. The number of entries is given by the value of amNumber.

amEntry.name: amEntry
amEntry.description: An acceleration monitor entry contains: the server IP address, server port and the status.

amIndex.name: amIndex
amIndex.description: A unique value for each entry in the acceleration monitor table.

amAddress.name: amAddress
amAddress.description: The IP address of the acceleration server the NetCache is monitoring.

amPort.name: amPort
amPort.description: The corresponding port on the server that NetCache is monitoring.

amStatus.name: amStatus
amStatus.description: The status of the service running on the server. active - in queue but no probes done yet. up - the server is reachable and responding to probes. down - the server is unreachable. inactive - monitoring is disabled.

ncLocalConfigChanged.name: ncLocalConfigChanged
ncLocalConfigChanged.description: Whether the local configuration file on NetCache was changed without using DFM configuration management.

grmMonitorToggle.name: grmMonitorToggle
grmMonitorToggle.description: Variable for user defined SNMP traps to monitor whether there has been a status change of any of the GRM agents reporting to this GRM server.

grmMonitorString.name: grmMonitorString
grmMonitorString.description: Used in conjunction with grmMonitor. This returns a string in format of: 'IP status.' which reports the status of all the GRM agents reporting to this GRM server as of last status change.

takeoverAddrs.name: takeoverAddrs
takeoverAddrs.description: Indicates the list of interfaces and their corresponding IP addresses of the partner NetCache that this appliance has taken over.

takeoverMode.name: takeoverMode
takeoverMode.description: Indicates the current takeover mode of this appliance.

takeoverStatus.name: takeoverStatus
takeoverStatus.description: Indicates the current status of the takeover partner of this appliance. up(1) indicates that the takeover partner is reachable. unknown(2) indicates that an unknown error occurred. failed(3) indicates that the partner has failed, takeoverAddrs indicates the partner's IP address this appliance has taken over.

nfsCacheBytesToClients.name: nfsCacheBytesToClients
nfsCacheBytesToClients.description: Total NFS bytes sent to clients

nfsCacheBytesFromServers.name: nfsCacheBytesFromServers
nfsCacheBytesFromServers.description: Total NFS bytes received from servers

nfsCacheBytesToServers.name: nfsCacheBytesToServers
nfsCacheBytesToServers.description: Total NFS bytes sent to servers

nfsCacheHitRequests.name: nfsCacheHitRequests
nfsCacheHitRequests.description: Total NFS requests resulting in cache hits

nfsCacheMissRequests.name: nfsCacheMissRequests
nfsCacheMissRequests.description: Total NFS requests resulting in cache misses

nfsCacheMissCacheableRequests.name: nfsCacheMissCacheableRequests
nfsCacheMissCacheableRequests.description: Total NFS requests that were cacheable misses

nfsCacheMissUnCacheableRequests.name: nfsCacheMissUnCacheableRequests
nfsCacheMissUnCacheableRequests.description: Total NFS requests that were uncacheable misses

nfsCacheEjectRequests.name: nfsCacheEjectRequests
nfsCacheEjectRequests.description: Total NFS requests resulting in object eject due to expiration

nfsCacheVerifyRequests.name: nfsCacheVerifyRequests
nfsCacheVerifyRequests.description: Total NFS requests resulting in object verification

nfsCacheHighBytesFromClients.name: nfsCacheHighBytesFromClients
nfsCacheHighBytesFromClients.description: Total NFS bytes received from clients. This object returns the most significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use nfsCache64BytesFromClients instead.

nfsCacheLowBytesFromClients.name: nfsCacheLowBytesFromClients
nfsCacheLowBytesFromClients.description: Total NFS bytes received from clients. This object returns the least significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use nfsCache64BytesFromClients instead.

nfsCacheHighBytesToClients.name: nfsCacheHighBytesToClients
nfsCacheHighBytesToClients.description: Total NFS bytes sent to clients. This object returns the most significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use nfsCache64BytesToClients instead.

nfsCacheLowBytesToClients.name: nfsCacheLowBytesToClients
nfsCacheLowBytesToClients.description: Total NFS bytes sent to clients. This object returns the least significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use nfsCache64BytesToClients instead.

nfsCacheHighBytesFromServers.name: nfsCacheHighBytesFromServers
nfsCacheHighBytesFromServers.description: Total NFS bytes received from servers. This object returns the most significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use nfsCache64BytesFromServers instead.

nfsCacheLowBytesFromServers.name: nfsCacheLowBytesFromServers
nfsCacheLowBytesFromServers.description: Total NFS bytes received from servers. This object returns the least significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use nfsCache64BytesFromServers instead.

nfsCacheHighBytesToServers.name: nfsCacheHighBytesToServers
nfsCacheHighBytesToServers.description: Total NFS bytes sent to servers. This object returns the most significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use nfsCache64BytesToServers instead.

nfsCacheLowBytesToServers.name: nfsCacheLowBytesToServers
nfsCacheLowBytesToServers.description: Total NFS bytes sent to servers. This object returns the least significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use nfsCache64BytesToServers instead.

nfsCacheHighTotalRequests.name: nfsCacheHighTotalRequests
nfsCacheHighTotalRequests.description: Total NFS requests received. This object returns the most significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use nfsCache64TotalRequests instead.

nfsCacheLowTotalRequests.name: nfsCacheLowTotalRequests
nfsCacheLowTotalRequests.description: Total NFS requests received. This object returns the least significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use nfsCache64TotalRequests instead.

nfsCacheHighHitRequests.name: nfsCacheHighHitRequests
nfsCacheHighHitRequests.description: Total NFS requests resulting in cache hits. This object returns the most significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use nfsCache64HitRequests instead.

nfsCacheLowHitRequests.name: nfsCacheLowHitRequests
nfsCacheLowHitRequests.description: Total NFS requests resulting in cache hits. This object returns the least significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use nfsCache64HitRequests instead.

nfsCacheHighMissRequests.name: nfsCacheHighMissRequests
nfsCacheHighMissRequests.description: Total NFS requests resulting in cache misses. This object returns the most significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use nfsCache64MissRequests instead.

nfsCacheLowMissRequests.name: nfsCacheLowMissRequests
nfsCacheLowMissRequests.description: Total NFS requests resulting in cache misses. This object returns the least significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use nfsCache64MissRequests instead.

nfsCache64BytesFromClients.name: nfsCache64BytesFromClients
nfsCache64BytesFromClients.description: Total NFS bytes received from clients. This object returns all of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

nfsCache64BytesToClients.name: nfsCache64BytesToClients
nfsCache64BytesToClients.description: Total NFS bytes sent to clients. This object returns all of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

nfsCache64BytesFromServers.name: nfsCache64BytesFromServers
nfsCache64BytesFromServers.description: Total NFS bytes received from servers. This object returns all of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

nfsCache64BytesToServers.name: nfsCache64BytesToServers
nfsCache64BytesToServers.description: Total NFS bytes sent to servers. This object returns all of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

nfsCache64TotalRequests.name: nfsCache64TotalRequests
nfsCache64TotalRequests.description: Total NFS requests received. This object returns all of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

nfsCache64HitRequests.name: nfsCache64HitRequests
nfsCache64HitRequests.description: Total NFS requests resulting in cache hits. This object returns all of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

nfsCache64MissRequests.name: nfsCache64MissRequests
nfsCache64MissRequests.description: Total NFS requests resulting in cache misses. This object returns all of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

enclNumber.name: enclNumber
enclNumber.description: The number of storage enclosures in the storage subsystem.

enclTable.name: enclTable
enclTable.description: Display disk enclosure environmental information for disk shelves that support SCSI Enclosure Services.

enclEntry.name: enclEntry
enclEntry.description: Display disk enclosure (shelf) environmental information for the referenced disk enclosure.

enclIndex.name: enclIndex
enclIndex.description: A number that identifies this enclosure among the possible monitored enclosures. This number normally uniquely identifies one shelf within one boot, but may it change between boots. The number may also change within a boot if shelves are removed and added.

enclContactState.name: enclContactState
enclContactState.description: The state of the communication between the filer or storage engine and the enclosure monitoring device in the enclosure.

enclChannelShelfAddr.name: enclChannelShelfAddr
enclChannelShelfAddr.description: The adapter number or switch name and the port number (together, called the channel), and shelf ID of this enclosure. Examples are 8a.1 and switch:5.1.

enclProductLogicalID.name: enclProductLogicalID
enclProductLogicalID.description: The logical identifier of this enclosure. This a form of the World-Wide Name (WWN).

enclProductID.name: enclProductID
enclProductID.description: The product ID of the shelf hardware module that provides the enclosure monitoring function. Example is LRC.

enclProductVendor.name: enclProductVendor
enclProductVendor.description: The name of the vendor of this enclosure. Example is Xyratex.

enclProductModel.name: enclProductModel
enclProductModel.description: The model name of this enclosure. Example is DiskShelf14.

enclProductRevision.name: enclProductRevision
enclProductRevision.description: The revision number of this enclosure.

enclProductSerialNo.name: enclProductSerialNo
enclProductSerialNo.description: The serial number of this enclosure.

enclNumberDiskBays.name: enclNumberDiskBays
enclNumberDiskBays.description: The number of disk bays in this enclosure.

enclDisksPresent.name: enclDisksPresent
enclDisksPresent.description: The list of disks present by bay number in this enclosure.

enclPowerSuppliesMaximum.name: enclPowerSuppliesMaximum
enclPowerSuppliesMaximum.description: The maximum number of power supplies in this enclosure.

enclPowerSuppliesPresent.name: enclPowerSuppliesPresent
enclPowerSuppliesPresent.description: The list of power supplies present in the enclosure. Numbering is from left to right (top supply, then bottom, on each side, if applicable) in their intended location in the shelf, while facing the supplies.

enclPowerSuppliesSerialNos.name: enclPowerSuppliesSerialNos
enclPowerSuppliesSerialNos.description: The list of serial numbers of power supplies present in the enclosure. Not all shelves are able to report the power supply serial number. Communication errors may make the serial number unavailable. The order follows that of enclPowerSuppliesPresent

enclPowerSuppliesFailed.name: enclPowerSuppliesFailed
enclPowerSuppliesFailed.description: The list of failed power supplies in this enclosure, numbered as in enclPowerSuppliesPresent.

enclFansMaximum.name: enclFansMaximum
enclFansMaximum.description: The maximum number of fans or fan modules monitored by this enclosure. R100/R150 shelf power supply fans are not included in this number.

enclFansPresent.name: enclFansPresent
enclFansPresent.description: The list of fans or fan modules present and for which status is known in this enclosure. Numbering begins with fans on the front of the enclosure, if applicable. Fans are numbered left-to-right (upper fans, then lower, if applicable) as facing the fans or the modules that contain them, such as power supply modules. R100/R150 shelf power supply fans are not included in this list.

enclFansFailed.name: enclFansFailed
enclFansFailed.description: The list of failed fans or fan modules in this enclosure. Fans are numbered as described in enclFansPresent.

enclTempSensorsMaximum.name: enclTempSensorsMaximum
enclTempSensorsMaximum.description: The maximum number of temperature sensors monitored by this enclosure.

enclTempSensorsPresent.name: enclTempSensorsPresent
enclTempSensorsPresent.description: The list of temperature sensors present and for which status is known in this enclosure. Temperature sensors are numbered top-to-bottom and left-to-right, beginning with the front of the enclosure, then the rear, as the modules containing them are faced.

enclTempSensorsOverTempFail.name: enclTempSensorsOverTempFail
enclTempSensorsOverTempFail.description: The list of temperature sensors reporting overtemperature failure in this enclosure. Sensors are numbered as in TempSensorsPresent.

enclTempSensorsOverTempWarn.name: enclTempSensorsOverTempWarn
enclTempSensorsOverTempWarn.description: The list of temperature sensors reporting overtemperature warning in this enclosure. Sensors are numbered as in TempSensorsPresent.

enclTempSensorsUnderTempFail.name: enclTempSensorsUnderTempFail
