enclTempSensorsUnderTempFail.description: The list of temperature sensors reporting undertemperature failure in this enclosure. Sensors are numbered as in TempSensorsPresent.

enclTempSensorsUnderTempWarn.name: enclTempSensorsUnderTempWarn
enclTempSensorsUnderTempWarn.description: The list of temperature sensors reporting undertemperature warning in this enclosure. Sensors are numbered as in TempSensorsPresent.

enclTempSensorsCurrentTemp.name: enclTempSensorsCurrentTemp
enclTempSensorsCurrentTemp.description: The list of temperatures reported by all temperature sensors in the enclosure, including the ambient temperature. Sensors are numbered as in TempSensorsPresent.

enclTempSensorsOverTempFailThr.name: enclTempSensorsOverTempFailThr
enclTempSensorsOverTempFailThr.description: The list of overtemperature failure thresholds for all temperature sensors in the enclosure. Sensors are numbered as in TempSensorsPresent.

enclTempSensorsOverTempWarnThr.name: enclTempSensorsOverTempWarnThr
enclTempSensorsOverTempWarnThr.description: The list of overtemperature warning thresholds for all temperature sensors in the enclosure. Sensors are numbered as in TempSensorsPresent.

enclTempSensorsUnderTempFailThr.name: enclTempSensorsUnderTempFailThr
enclTempSensorsUnderTempFailThr.description: The list of undertemperature failure thresholds for all temperature sensors in the enclosure. Sensors are numbered as in TempSensorsPresent.

enclTempSensorsUnderTempWarnThr.name: enclTempSensorsUnderTempWarnThr
enclTempSensorsUnderTempWarnThr.description: The list of undertemperature warning thresholds for all temperature sensors in the enclosure. Sensors are numbered as in TempSensorsPresent.

enclElectronicsMaximum.name: enclElectronicsMaximum
enclElectronicsMaximum.description: The number of enclosure services electronics modules that it is possible for this enclosure to detect and/or monitor.

enclElectronicsPresent.name: enclElectronicsPresent
enclElectronicsPresent.description: The list those enclosure services electronics modules present in this enclosure. Numbering is from left-to-right or top-to-bottom in their intended location in the shelf, while facing the electronics modules. It is normal for the R200 FC-AT module to be reported as the second module.

enclElectronicsSerialNos.name: enclElectronicsSerialNos
enclElectronicsSerialNos.description: The list of serial numbers of the enclosure services electronics modules present in this enclosure. The order follows that of enclElectronicsPresent.

enclElectronicsFailed.name: enclElectronicsFailed
enclElectronicsFailed.description: The list of failed electronics elements. Valid only if enclElectronicsPresent shows that some are present.

enclVoltSensorsMaximum.name: enclVoltSensorsMaximum
enclVoltSensorsMaximum.description: The number of voltage sensors monitored by this enclosure.

enclVoltSensorsPresent.name: enclVoltSensorsPresent
enclVoltSensorsPresent.description: The list of voltage sensors present and for which status is known in this enclosure. Voltage sensors are numbered top-to-bottom and left-to-right, as the modules containing them are faced.

enclVoltSensorsOverVoltFail.name: enclVoltSensorsOverVoltFail
enclVoltSensorsOverVoltFail.description: The list of voltage sensors reporting overvoltage failure in this enclosure. Sensors are numbered as in VoltSensorsPresent.

enclVoltSensorsOverVoltWarn.name: enclVoltSensorsOverVoltWarn
enclVoltSensorsOverVoltWarn.description: The list of voltage sensors reporting overvoltage warning in this enclosure. Sensors are numbered as in VoltSensorsPresent.

enclVoltSensorsUnderVoltFail.name: enclVoltSensorsUnderVoltFail
enclVoltSensorsUnderVoltFail.description: The list of voltage sensors reporting undervoltage failure in this enclosure. Sensors are numbered as in VoltSensorsPresent.

enclVoltSensorsUnderVoltWarn.name: enclVoltSensorsUnderVoltWarn
enclVoltSensorsUnderVoltWarn.description: The list of voltage sensors reporting undervoltage warning in this enclosure. Sensors are numbered as in VoltSensorsPresent.

enclVoltSensorsCurrentVolt.name: enclVoltSensorsCurrentVolt
enclVoltSensorsCurrentVolt.description: The list of voltages reported by all voltage sensors in the enclosure, Sensors are numbered as in VoltSensorsPresent.

enclVoltSensorsOverVoltFailThr.name: enclVoltSensorsOverVoltFailThr
enclVoltSensorsOverVoltFailThr.description: The list of overvoltage failure thresholds for all voltage sensors in the enclosure. Sensors are numbered as in VoltSensorsPresent.

enclVoltSensorsOverVoltWarnThr.name: enclVoltSensorsOverVoltWarnThr
enclVoltSensorsOverVoltWarnThr.description: The list of overvoltage warning thresholds for all voltage sensors in the enclosure. Sensors are numbered as in VoltSensorsPresent.

enclVoltSensorsUnderVoltFailThr.name: enclVoltSensorsUnderVoltFailThr
enclVoltSensorsUnderVoltFailThr.description: The list of undervoltage failure thresholds for all voltage sensors in the enclosure. Sensors are numbered as in VoltSensorsPresent.

enclVoltSensorsUnderVoltWarnThr.name: enclVoltSensorsUnderVoltWarnThr
enclVoltSensorsUnderVoltWarnThr.description: The list of undervoltage warning thresholds for all voltage sensors in the enclosure. Sensors are numbered as in VoltSensorsPresent.

enclCurSensorsMaximum.name: enclCurSensorsMaximum
enclCurSensorsMaximum.description: The number of current sensors monitored by this enclosure.

enclCurSensorsPresent.name: enclCurSensorsPresent
enclCurSensorsPresent.description: The list of current sensors present and for which status is known in this enclosure. Current sensors are numbered top-to-bottom and left-to-right, beginning with the front of the enclosure, then the rear, as the modules containing them are faced.

enclCurSensorsOverCurFail.name: enclCurSensorsOverCurFail
enclCurSensorsOverCurFail.description: The list of current sensors reporting overcurrent failure in this enclosure. Sensors are numbered as in CurSensorsPresent.

enclCurSensorsOverCurWarn.name: enclCurSensorsOverCurWarn
enclCurSensorsOverCurWarn.description: The list of current sensors reporting overcurrent warning in this enclosure. Sensors are numbered as in CurSensorsPresent.

enclCurSensorsCurrentCur.name: enclCurSensorsCurrentCur
enclCurSensorsCurrentCur.description: The list of currents reported by all current sensors in the enclosure, Sensors are numbered as in CurSensorsPresent.

enclCurSensorsOverCurFailThr.name: enclCurSensorsOverCurFailThr
enclCurSensorsOverCurFailThr.description: The list of overcurrent failure thresholds for all current sensors in the enclosure. Sensors are numbered as in CurSensorsPresent.

enclCurSensorsOverCurWarnThr.name: enclCurSensorsOverCurWarnThr
enclCurSensorsOverCurWarnThr.description: The list of overcurrent warning thresholds for all current sensors in the enclosure. Sensors are numbered as in CurSensorsPresent.

enclSASConnectMaximum.name: enclSASConnectMaximum
enclSASConnectMaximum.description: The number of possible SAS connectors monitored by this enclosure.

enclSASConnectPresent.name: enclSASConnectPresent
enclSASConnectPresent.description: The list of SAS connector numbers in this enclosure that have cables attached. Connectors are numbered beginning at one on module one, counting connectors innermost-to-outermost on the module, then module two innermost-to-outermost. Modules are numbered as in enclElectronicsPresent.

enclSASConnectVendor.name: enclSASConnectVendor
enclSASConnectVendor.description: The list of vendors of cables attached to the SES connectors of the enclosure. If no cable, is attached, the entry is shown as <N/A>.

enclSASConnectType.name: enclSASConnectType
enclSASConnectType.description: The list of connector types of connectors attached to the enclosure. If no cable is attached, the entry is shown as <N/A>.

enclSASConnectCableLen.name: enclSASConnectCableLen
enclSASConnectCableLen.description: The list of lengths (in meters) of cables attached to the enclosure. If no cable is attached, the entry is shown as <N/A>.

enclSASConnectCableTech.name: enclSASConnectCableTech
enclSASConnectCableTech.description: The list of cable technologies of connectors attached to the enclosure. If no cable is attached, the entry is shown as <N/A>.

enclSASConnectCableEnd.name: enclSASConnectCableEnd
enclSASConnectCableEnd.description: The list of identifiers of which end of the cable is attached to the enclosure. If no cable is attached, the entry is shown as <N/A>.

enclSASConnectSerialNos.name: enclSASConnectSerialNos
enclSASConnectSerialNos.description: The list of serial numbers of the SAS cables attached to this enclosure. If no cable is attached, the entry is shown as <N/A>.

enclSASConnectPartNos.name: enclSASConnectPartNos
enclSASConnectPartNos.description: The list of part numbers of the SAS cables attached to this enclosure. If no cable is attached, the entry is shown as <N/A>.

enclPowerSuppliesPartNos.name: enclPowerSuppliesPartNos
enclPowerSuppliesPartNos.description: The list of part numbers of power supplies present in the enclosure. Not all shelves are able to report the power supply part number. Communication errors may make the part number unavailable. The order follows that of enclPowerSuppliesPresent.

enclFansSpeed.name: enclFansSpeed
enclFansSpeed.description: The list of fan speeds in revolutions per minute (RPM) for fans or fan modules present and for which speed status is known in this enclosure. Not all enclosure types report fan speeds. Fans are numbered as described in enclFansPresent.

enclElectronicsPartNos.name: enclElectronicsPartNos
enclElectronicsPartNos.description: The list of part numbers of the enclosure services electronics modules present in this enclosure. The order follows that of enclElectronicsPresent.

enclElectronicsCPLDVers.name: enclElectronicsCPLDVers
enclElectronicsCPLDVers.description: The list of CPLDs ('complex programmable logic devices') of the enclosure services electronics modules present in this enclosure. Not all module types contain this part. The order follows that of enclElectronicsPresent.

enclNodeName.name: enclNodeName
enclNodeName.description: Node to which this enclosure belongs.

haTable.name: haTable
haTable.description: High Availability configuration information table. This table fields are returned only from the cluster interfaces

haSettings.name: haSettings
haSettings.description: High Availability configuration settings. The value notConfigured(1) indicates that the HA is not licensed. The thisNodeDead(5) setting indicates that this node has been takenover.

haCannotTakeoverCause.name: haCannotTakeoverCause
haCannotTakeoverCause.description: The reason node cannot takeover its HA partner

haPartnerStatus.name: haPartnerStatus
haPartnerStatus.description: This is the status last returned by its HA partner.

haPartnerLastStatusUpdate.name: haPartnerLastStatusUpdate
haPartnerLastStatusUpdate.description: If non-zero, the absolute time of the last update from the partner.

haInterconnectStatus.name: haInterconnectStatus
haInterconnectStatus.description: The current status of the interconnect. The partialFailure(3) status indicates that one of the links in the interconnect hardware is down.

netifNumber.name: netifNumber
netifNumber.description: The number of network interfaces (regardless of their current state) present on this system.

netifTable.name: netifTable
netifTable.description: A list of interface entries. The number of entries is given by the value of netifNumber.

netifEntry.name: netifEntry
netifEntry.description: An interface entry containing objects at the subnetwork layer and below for a particular interface.

netifIndex.name: netifIndex
netifIndex.description: A unique value for each interface. For clustered Data ONTAP, the high-order 16-bits denote the node identifier and the low-order 16-bits denote the interface index within the node. For Data ONTAP operating in 7-mode, it ranges between 1 and the ifNumber value. The value for each interface must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re-initialization.

netifDescr.name: netifDescr
netifDescr.description: A textual string that contains interface information. For clustered Data ONTAP, the string is in the the following format: <node name>:<interface name> For Data ONTAP operating in 7-Mode, the string contains only the interface name. For a management port (for example, e0M or e0P), the interface name is preceded by the text MGMT_PORT_ONLY and a blank space after the text, in both clustered Data ONTAP and Data ONTAP operating in 7-Mode. Example: The strings are in the following formats: <node name>:MGMT_PORT_ONLY <interface name>, for clustered Data ONTAP. MGMT_PORT_ONLY <interface name>, for Data ONTAP operating in 7-mode.

ifHighInOctets.name: ifHighInOctets
ifHighInOctets.description: The total number of octets received on the interface, including framing characters. This object returns the most significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use if64InOctets instead.

ifLowInOctets.name: ifLowInOctets
ifLowInOctets.description: The total number of octets received on the interface, including framing characters. This object returns the least significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use if64InOctets instead.

ifHighInUcastPkts.name: ifHighInUcastPkts
ifHighInUcastPkts.description: The number of subnetwork-unicast packets delivered to a higher-layer protocol. This object returns the most significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use if64InUcastPkts instead.

ifLowInUcastPkts.name: ifLowInUcastPkts
ifLowInUcastPkts.description: The number of subnetwork-unicast packets delivered to a higher-layer protocol. This object returns the least significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use if64InUcastPkts instead.

ifHighInNUcastPkts.name: ifHighInNUcastPkts
ifHighInNUcastPkts.description: The number of non-unicast (i.e., subnetwork- broadcast or subnetwork-multicast) packets delivered to a higher-layer protocol. This object returns the most significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use if64InNUcastPkts instead.

ifLowInNUcastPkts.name: ifLowInNUcastPkts
ifLowInNUcastPkts.description: The number of non-unicast (i.e., subnetwork- broadcast or subnetwork-multicast) packets delivered to a higher-layer protocol. This object returns the least significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use if64InNUcastPkts instead.

ifHighInDiscards.name: ifHighInDiscards
ifHighInDiscards.description: The number of inbound packets which were chosen to be discarded even though no errors had been detected to prevent their being deliverable to a higher-layer protocol. One possible reason for discarding such a packet could be to free up buffer space. This object returns the most significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use if64InDiscards instead.

ifLowInDiscards.name: ifLowInDiscards
ifLowInDiscards.description: The number of inbound packets which were chosen to be discarded even though no errors had been detected to prevent their being deliverable to a higher-layer protocol. One possible reason for discarding such a packet could be to free up buffer space. This object returns the least significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use if64InDiscards instead.

ifHighInErrors.name: ifHighInErrors
ifHighInErrors.description: The number of inbound packets that contained errors preventing them from being deliverable to a higher-layer protocol. This object returns the most significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use if64InErrors instead.

ifLowInErrors.name: ifLowInErrors
ifLowInErrors.description: The number of inbound packets that contained errors preventing them from being deliverable to a higher-layer protocol. This object returns the least significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use if64InErrors instead.

ifHighInUnknownProtos.name: ifHighInUnknownProtos
ifHighInUnknownProtos.description: The number of packets received via the interface which were discarded because of an unknown or unsupported protocol. This object returns the most significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use if64InUnknownProtos instead.

ifLowInUnknownProtos.name: ifLowInUnknownProtos
ifLowInUnknownProtos.description: The number of packets received via the interface which were discarded because of an unknown or unsupported protocol. This object returns the least significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use if64InUnknownProtos instead.

ifHighOutOctets.name: ifHighOutOctets
ifHighOutOctets.description: The total number of octets transmitted out of the interface, including framing characters. This object returns the most significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use if64OutOctets instead.

ifLowOutOctets.name: ifLowOutOctets
ifLowOutOctets.description: The total number of octets transmitted out of the interface, including framing characters. This object returns the least significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use if64OutOctets instead.

ifHighOutUcastPkts.name: ifHighOutUcastPkts
ifHighOutUcastPkts.description: The total number of packets that higher-level protocols requested be transmitted to a subnetwork-unicast address, including those that were discarded or not sent. This object returns the most significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use if64OutUcastPkts instead.

ifLowOutUcastPkts.name: ifLowOutUcastPkts
ifLowOutUcastPkts.description: The total number of packets that higher-level protocols requested be transmitted to a subnetwork-unicast address, including those that were discarded or not sent. This object returns the least significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use if64OutUcastPkts instead.

ifHighOutNUcastPkts.name: ifHighOutNUcastPkts
ifHighOutNUcastPkts.description: The total number of packets that higher-level protocols requested be transmitted to a non- unicast (i.e., a subnetwork-broadcast or subnetwork-multicast) address, including those that were discarded or not sent. This object returns the most significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use if64OutNUcastPkts instead.

ifLowOutNUcastPkts.name: ifLowOutNUcastPkts
ifLowOutNUcastPkts.description: The total number of packets that higher-level protocols requested be transmitted to a non- unicast (i.e., a subnetwork-broadcast or subnetwork-multicast) address, including those that were discarded or not sent. This object returns the least significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use if64OutNUcastPkts instead.

ifHighOutDiscards.name: ifHighOutDiscards
ifHighOutDiscards.description: The number of outbound packets which were chosen to be discarded even though no errors had been detected to prevent their being transmitted. One possible reason for discarding such a packet could be to free up buffer space. This object returns the most significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use if64OutDiscards instead.

ifLowOutDiscards.name: ifLowOutDiscards
ifLowOutDiscards.description: The number of outbound packets which were chosen to be discarded even though no errors had been detected to prevent their being transmitted. One possible reason for discarding such a packet could be to free up buffer space. This object returns the least significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use if64OutDiscards instead.

ifHighOutErrors.name: ifHighOutErrors
ifHighOutErrors.description: The number of outbound packets that could not be transmitted because of errors. This object returns the most significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use if64OutErrors instead.

ifLowOutErrors.name: ifLowOutErrors
ifLowOutErrors.description: The number of outbound packets that could not be transmitted because of errors. This object returns the least significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use if64OutErrors instead.

if64InOctets.name: if64InOctets
if64InOctets.description: The total number of octets received on the interface, including framing characters. This object returns all of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

if64InUcastPkts.name: if64InUcastPkts
if64InUcastPkts.description: The number of subnetwork-unicast packets delivered to a higher-layer protocol. This object returns all of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

if64InNUcastPkts.name: if64InNUcastPkts
if64InNUcastPkts.description: The number of non-unicast (i.e., subnetwork- broadcast or subnetwork-multicast) packets delivered to a higher-layer protocol. This object returns all of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

if64InDiscards.name: if64InDiscards
if64InDiscards.description: The number of inbound packets which were chosen to be discarded even though no errors had been detected to prevent their being deliverable to a higher-layer protocol. One possible reason for discarding such a packet could be to free up buffer space. This object returns all of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

if64InErrors.name: if64InErrors
if64InErrors.description: The number of inbound packets that contained errors preventing them from being deliverable to a higher-layer protocol. This object returns all of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

if64InUnknownProtos.name: if64InUnknownProtos
if64InUnknownProtos.description: The number of packets received via the interface which were discarded because of an unknown or unsupported protocol. This object returns all of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

if64OutOctets.name: if64OutOctets
if64OutOctets.description: The total number of octets transmitted out of the interface, including framing characters. This object returns all of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

if64OutUcastPkts.name: if64OutUcastPkts
if64OutUcastPkts.description: The total number of packets that higher-level protocols requested be transmitted to a subnetwork-unicast address, including those that were discarded or not sent. This object returns all of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

if64OutNUcastPkts.name: if64OutNUcastPkts
if64OutNUcastPkts.description: The total number of packets that higher-level protocols requested be transmitted to a non- unicast (i.e., a subnetwork-broadcast or subnetwork-multicast) address, including those that were discarded or not sent. This object returns all of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

if64OutDiscards.name: if64OutDiscards
if64OutDiscards.description: The number of outbound packets which were chosen to be discarded even though no errors had been detected to prevent their being transmitted. One possible reason for discarding such a packet could be to free up buffer space. This object returns all of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

if64OutErrors.name: if64OutErrors
if64OutErrors.description: The number of outbound packets that could not be transmitted because of errors. This object returns all of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

netportTable.name: netportTable
netportTable.description: A list of network ports (both physical and logical) on all nodes in the cluster.

netportNode.name: netportNode
netportNode.description: Node where the port belongs to.

netportRole.name: netportRole
netportRole.description: Role of the port. A port must have one of the following roles: cluster(1), data(2), mgmt(3), intercluster(4), cluster-mgmt(5) or undef(0). The cluster port is used to communicate to other node(s) in the cluster. The data port services clients' requests. It is where all the file requests come in. The management port is used by administrator to manage resources within a node. The intercluster port is used to communicate to other cluster. The cluster-mgmt port is used to manage resources within the cluster. The undef role is for the port that has not yet been assigned a role.

netportLinkState.name: netportLinkState
netportLinkState.description: The link-state of the port. Normally it is either UP(2) or DOWN(3).

netportMtu.name: netportMtu
netportMtu.description: The Maximum Transmission Unit (MTU) refers to the size (in bytes) of the largest packet that is supported by the port.

netportAutonegAdmin.name: netportAutonegAdmin
netportAutonegAdmin.description: Indicates whether the port's auto-negotiation property is enabled by an administrator.

netportAutonegOper.name: netportAutonegOper
netportAutonegOper.description: Indicates whether the auto-negotiation is enabled on the port.

netportDuplexAdmin.name: netportDuplexAdmin
netportDuplexAdmin.description: The duplex mode of the port set by the administrator. It can be either undef(0), auto(1), half-duplex(2), or full-duplex(3).

netportDuplexOper.name: netportDuplexOper
netportDuplexOper.description: The duplex mode appears on the port. It can be either undef(0), auto(1), half-duplex(2), or full-duplex(3).

netportSpeedAdmin.name: netportSpeedAdmin
netportSpeedAdmin.description: The speed of the port set by an administrator. It can be either undef(0), auto(1), ten Mb/s(2), hundred Mb/s(3), one Gb/s(4), or ten Gb/s(5).

netportSpeedOper.name: netportSpeedOper
netportSpeedOper.description: The speed appears on the port. It can be either undef(0), auto(1), ten Mb/s(2), hundred Mb/s(3), one Gb/s(4), or ten Gb/s(5).

netportSpeed.name: netportSpeed
netportSpeed.description: The speed that appears in the port scaled to megabits/sec.

netportUpAdmin.name: netportUpAdmin
netportUpAdmin.description: Indicates whether the port status is set 'UP' by an administrator.

netportType.name: netportType
netportType.description: The type of the port which can be either physical(0), if-group(1), vlan(2) or undef(3).

netportIfgNode.name: netportIfgNode
netportIfgNode.description: This field shows the if-group node name if the port type is if-group, It show an empty string, otherwise.

netportIfgPort.name: netportIfgPort
netportIfgPort.description: This field shows the if-group port if the port type is if-group, It show an empty string, otherwise.

netportIfgDistrFunc.name: netportIfgDistrFunc
netportIfgDistrFunc.description: If the port type is if-group, this field shows the distribution function of the port. This function is used to pick the forwarding port for a packet. It can be either mac(0), ip(1), or sequential(2). The mac function selects the port based on the hash of the MAC address of the destination. Instead of MAC address, the ip function uses the destination's IP address. The sequential function uses the round-robin port selection.

netportIfgMode.name: netportIfgMode
netportIfgMode.description: If the port type is if-group, this field shows the if-group's policy. It can be either multimode(0), multimode-lacp(1), or single-mode(2). Otherwise, it shows an empty string. The multimode policy uses the static link-aggregation, while the multimode-lacp uses the link-aggregation with lacp (Link Aggregate Control Protocol). The single mode does not use link-aggregation.

netportVlanNode.name: netportVlanNode
netportVlanNode.description: If the port type is vlan, this field shows its vlan node. Otherwise, it shows an empty string.

netportVlanPort.name: netportVlanPort
netportVlanPort.description: If the port type is vlan, this field shows its vlan port. Otherwise, it shows an empty string.

netportVlanTag.name: netportVlanTag
netportVlanTag.description: If the port type is vlan, this field shows its vlan tag. Otherwise, it shows an empty string.

netportFlowcontrolAdmin.name: netportFlowcontrolAdmin
netportFlowcontrolAdmin.description: The flowcontrol of the port set by an administrator. It can be either undef(0), none(1), receive(2), send(3), or full(4).

netportFlowcontrolOper.name: netportFlowcontrolOper
netportFlowcontrolOper.description: The flowcontrol that appears on the port. It can be either undef(0), none(1), receive(2), send(3), or full(4).

netportAutorevertDelay.name: netportAutorevertDelay
netportAutorevertDelay.description: If the port is designated as a cluster port, this field shows the delay in seconds before auto reverting a LIF to this port. otherwise, it shows an empty string.

netportRemoteDeviceId.name: netportRemoteDeviceId
netportRemoteDeviceId.description: Remote device ID discovered by L2 protocol.

netportIPspace.name: netportIPspace
netportIPspace.description: IPspace where the port is assigned.

netportBroadcastDomain.name: netportBroadcastDomain
netportBroadcastDomain.description: Broadcast Domain of the port is assigned.

netportMtuAdmin.name: netportMtuAdmin
netportMtuAdmin.description: The Maximum Transmission Unit (MTU) set by the Administrator (in bytes) of the largest packet that is supported by the port.

netportIfGrpTable.name: netportIfGrpTable
netportIfGrpTable.description: A table of if-groups, where each entry represents an interface of the group.

netportIfGrpNode.name: netportIfGrpNode
netportIfGrpNode.description: The node that the If-group belongs to.

netportIfGrpDistrFunc.name: netportIfGrpDistrFunc
netportIfGrpDistrFunc.description: The distribute function of the if-group. This function is used to pick the forwarding port for a packet. It can be either mac(0), ip(1), or sequential(2). The mac function selects the port based on the hash of the MAC address of the destination. Instead of MAC address, the ip function uses IP address. The sequential function uses the round-robin port selection.

netportIfGrpMode.name: netportIfGrpMode
netportIfGrpMode.description: The policy of the if-group. It can be either multimode(0), multimode-lacp(1), or single-mode(2). The multimode policy uses the static link-aggregation, while the multimode-lacp uses the link-aggregation with lacp (Link Aggregate Control Protocol). The single mode does not use link-aggregation.

netportIfGrpMac.name: netportIfGrpMac
netportIfGrpMac.description: The MAC address of the if-group.

netportIfGrpActivePorts.name: netportIfGrpActivePorts
netportIfGrpActivePorts.description: The participation of the network ports in the if-group. It can be full, partial, and none.

netportIfGrpPorts.name: netportIfGrpPorts
netportIfGrpPorts.description: A list of network ports that participate in the if-group.

netportIfGrpUpPorts.name: netportIfGrpUpPorts
netportIfGrpUpPorts.description: A list of network ports that are 'UP' in the if-group.

netportIfGrpDownPorts.name: netportIfGrpDownPorts
netportIfGrpDownPorts.description: A list of network ports that are 'DOWN' in the if-group.

logicalInterfaceTable.name: logicalInterfaceTable
logicalInterfaceTable.description: A list of logical interface entries.

logicalInterfaceServer.name: logicalInterfaceServer
logicalInterfaceServer.description: The node where the logical interface belongs to.

logicalInterfaceVif.name: logicalInterfaceVif
logicalInterfaceVif.description: The name of the logical interface.

logicalInterfaceRole.name: logicalInterfaceRole
logicalInterfaceRole.description: The role of logical interface. An interface can have one of the following roles: undef(0), cluster(1), data(2), mgmt(3), intercluster(4), and cluster-mgmt(5). The cluster interface is used to communicate to other node(s) in the cluster. The data interface services external clients where all the file requests come in. The management interface is used by administrator to manage resources within a node. The intercluster interface is used to communicate to other cluster. The cluster-mgmt port is used to manage resources within the cluster. The undef role is for the interface that has not yet been assigned a role.

logicalInterfaceHomeNode.name: logicalInterfaceHomeNode
logicalInterfaceHomeNode.description: The home node of the interface where the interface is initially setup.

logicalInterfaceHomePort.name: logicalInterfaceHomePort
logicalInterfaceHomePort.description: The home port of the interface where the interface is initially setup.

logicalInterfaceCurrNode.name: logicalInterfaceCurrNode
logicalInterfaceCurrNode.description: The node where the interface is currently on.

logicalInterfaceCurrPort.name: logicalInterfaceCurrPort
logicalInterfaceCurrPort.description: The port where the interface is currently attached to.

logicalInterfaceStatusOper.name: logicalInterfaceStatusOper
logicalInterfaceStatusOper.description: The operational status, which can be UP(0) or DOWN(1).

logicalInterfaceIsHome.name: logicalInterfaceIsHome
logicalInterfaceIsHome.description: Indicates whether the interface is at the home node.

logicalInterfaceAddress.name: logicalInterfaceAddress
logicalInterfaceAddress.description: The IP address assigned to the interface. This field only displays ipv4 addresses correctly. Ipv6 addresses will display as 0.0.0.0. Refer to the logicalInterfaceAddressString field for the address of an ipv6 interface.

logicalInterfaceNetmask.name: logicalInterfaceNetmask
logicalInterfaceNetmask.description: The netmask assigned to the interface. This field only displays ipv4 netmasks correctly. Ipv6 netmasks will display as 0.0.0.0. Refer to the logicalInterfaceAddressString field for the netmask length of an ipv6 interface.

logicalInterfaceNetmaskLength.name: logicalInterfaceNetmaskLength
logicalInterfaceNetmaskLength.description: The number of set bits of the netmask.

logicalInterfaceStatusAdmin.name: logicalInterfaceStatusAdmin
logicalInterfaceStatusAdmin.description: The status of the interface assigned by an administrator. It can be either UP(0) or DOWN(1).

logicalInterfaceFailoverPolicy.name: logicalInterfaceFailoverPolicy
logicalInterfaceFailoverPolicy.description: The interface's failover policy. It can be next-available(0), where the interface will failover to any next available interface, priority(1), where the interface will failover to the interface that has the highest priority, or disabled(2).

logicalInterfaceFirewallPolicy.name: logicalInterfaceFirewallPolicy
logicalInterfaceFirewallPolicy.description: The firewall policy of the interface.

logicalInterfaceAutoRevert.name: logicalInterfaceAutoRevert
logicalInterfaceAutoRevert.description: Indicates whether the auto-revert property of the interface is set. If the value is 'true', the interface will automatically revert back to the home port whenever the interface is not on the home port and the home port becomes operational.

logicalInterfaceSticky.name: logicalInterfaceSticky
logicalInterfaceSticky.description: Indicates whether the sticky bit is set. It is the readonly field that is set by the system. When it is set, the interface's auto-revert is disabled. It is set when the interface is migrated manually, so that it will not auto-revert to the home port.

logicalInterfaceUseFailoverGroup.name: logicalInterfaceUseFailoverGroup
logicalInterfaceUseFailoverGroup.description: The field identifies whether the interface's failover is system-defined(0), set to 'enabled'(1) or 'disable'(2).

logicalInterfaceAllowLbMigrate.name: logicalInterfaceAllowLbMigrate
logicalInterfaceAllowLbMigrate.description: Indicates whether the load balancing migration is enabled for the interface.

logicalInterfaceLbWeight.name: logicalInterfaceLbWeight
logicalInterfaceLbWeight.description: The load balancing weight of the interface. It can be either minimum (0), maximum(100), or load(101).

logicalInterfaceStatusVserver.name: logicalInterfaceStatusVserver
logicalInterfaceStatusVserver.description: The status of the interface with respect to its Vserver. It can be either UP(0) or DOWN(1).

logicalInterfaceFcpWwpn.name: logicalInterfaceFcpWwpn
logicalInterfaceFcpWwpn.description: The WWPN of a FCP data LIF.

logicalInterfaceComment.name: logicalInterfaceComment
logicalInterfaceComment.description: A comment to further identify a LIF.

logicalInterfaceListenForDnsQuery.name: logicalInterfaceListenForDnsQuery
logicalInterfaceListenForDnsQuery.description: Indicates whether the LIF has to listen for DNS queries for load-balancing.

logicalInterfaceAddressString.name: logicalInterfaceAddressString
logicalInterfaceAddressString.description: The IP address assigned to the interface. This field displays properly for both ipv4 addresses as well as ipv6 addresses. Format: <ip address>/<netmask length>

netOptsv6Enabled.name: netOptsv6Enabled
netOptsv6Enabled.description: Indicates whether the cluster supports IPv6.

netOptsv6RAProcEnabled.name: netOptsv6RAProcEnabled
netOptsv6RAProcEnabled.description: Indicates whether the cluster supports IPv6 Router Advertisement Processing.

netOptsSwitchlessClusterEnabled.name: netOptsSwitchlessClusterEnabled
netOptsSwitchlessClusterEnabled.description: Indicates whether the cluster network is switchless.

ipspaceTable.name: ipspaceTable
ipspaceTable.description: A table of IPspaces, where each entry represents an IPspace.

ipspacePorts.name: ipspacePorts
ipspacePorts.description: The network ports assigned to the IPspace of the form {node1:port1},{node2:port2}.

ipspaceBroadcastDomains.name: ipspaceBroadcastDomains
ipspaceBroadcastDomains.description: The broadcast domains for the IPspace.

ipspaceVservers.name: ipspaceVservers
ipspaceVservers.description: The vservers assigned to the IPspace of the form {vs1,vs2}.

vsRouteTable.name: vsRouteTable
vsRouteTable.description: A table of vserver routes, where each entry represents a vserver route.

vsRouteVserverID.name: vsRouteVserverID
vsRouteVserverID.description: The vserver of the vserver route.

vsRouteUuid.name: vsRouteUuid
vsRouteUuid.description: The Uuid of the vserver route.

vsRouteDestination.name: vsRouteDestination
vsRouteDestination.description: The destination of the vserver route.

vsRouteGateway.name: vsRouteGateway
vsRouteGateway.description: The gateway of the vserver route.

vsRouteMetric.name: vsRouteMetric
vsRouteMetric.description: The metric of the vserver route.

vsRouteAddressFamily.name: vsRouteAddressFamily
vsRouteAddressFamily.description: The address family of the vserver route.

vsFailoverGroupTable.name: vsFailoverGroupTable
vsFailoverGroupTable.description: A table of logical interface failover groups, where each entry represents a logical interface failover group.

vsFailoverGroupVserverID.name: vsFailoverGroupVserverID
vsFailoverGroupVserverID.description: The vserver of the failover group.

vsFailoverGroupName.name: vsFailoverGroupName
vsFailoverGroupName.description: The name of the failover group.

vsFailoverGroupTargets.name: vsFailoverGroupTargets
vsFailoverGroupTargets.description: The failover targets of the failover group.

vsFirewallPolicyTable.name: vsFirewallPolicyTable
vsFirewallPolicyTable.description: A table of firewall policies, where each entry represents a firewall policy.

vsFirewallPolicyVserverID.name: vsFirewallPolicyVserverID
vsFirewallPolicyVserverID.description: The vserver on which this firewall policy is defined.

vsFirewallPolicyUuid.name: vsFirewallPolicyUuid
vsFirewallPolicyUuid.description: The unique identifier for this firewall policy.

vsFirewallPolicyName.name: vsFirewallPolicyName
vsFirewallPolicyName.description: The name of this firewall policy.

vsFirewallPolicyService.name: vsFirewallPolicyService
vsFirewallPolicyService.description: The service that this firewall policy is restricting access to.

vsFirewallPolicyAllowList.name: vsFirewallPolicyAllowList
vsFirewallPolicyAllowList.description: The list of source IPs that are allowed to access the underlying service of this firewall policy.

broadcastDomainTable.name: broadcastDomainTable
broadcastDomainTable.description: A table of broadcast domains, where each entry represents a broadcast domain.

broadcastDomainPorts.name: broadcastDomainPorts
broadcastDomainPorts.description: The network ports assigned to the broadcast domain of the form {node1:port1},{node2:port2}.

broadcastDomainFailoverGroups.name: broadcastDomainFailoverGroups
broadcastDomainFailoverGroups.description: The failover groups for the broadcast domain of the form {fg1,fg2}.

broadcastDomainSubnets.name: broadcastDomainSubnets
broadcastDomainSubnets.description: The subnets associated with this broadcast domain.

subnetTable.name: subnetTable
subnetTable.description: A table of Subnets, where each entry represents a Subnet.

subnetTotalCount.name: subnetTotalCount
subnetTotalCount.description: Total address count for all ranges.

subnetUsedCount.name: subnetUsedCount
subnetUsedCount.description: Used address count for all ranges.

subnetAvailableCount.name: subnetAvailableCount
subnetAvailableCount.description: Available address count for all ranges.

sisIsLicensed.name: sisIsLicensed
sisIsLicensed.description: Indicates whether Advanced SIS is licensed on the filer.

sisTable.name: sisTable
sisTable.description: Provide a list of the SIS volumes on the system.

sisEntry.name: sisEntry
sisEntry.description: Provide details about a particular SIS volume. For entries returned only from the cluster interfaces, the value of sisRowAvailable needs to be 1, for the contents of the row to be valid.

sisIndex.name: sisIndex
sisIndex.description: A number that identifies this entry for the SIS volume.

sisPath.name: sisPath
sisPath.description: The path to the SIS volume.

sisState.name: sisState
sisState.description: Indicates whether SIS is enabled on the volume or not.

sisStatus.name: sisStatus
sisStatus.description: Current status of the SIS volume.

sisProgress.name: sisProgress
sisProgress.description: The progress of the current SIS operation.

sisType.name: sisType
sisType.description: Indicates whether it is a regular or snapvaulted SIS volume.

sisSchedule.name: sisSchedule
sisSchedule.description: The schedule for the SIS operations.

sisLastOpBeginTime.name: sisLastOpBeginTime
sisLastOpBeginTime.description: The starting time of the last completed SIS operation.

sisLastOpEndTime.name: sisLastOpEndTime
sisLastOpEndTime.description: The ending time of the last completed SIS operation.

sisHighLastOpSize.name: sisHighLastOpSize
sisHighLastOpSize.description: The total amount of data in KBytes that the last completed SIS operation had processed. This object returns the most significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use sis64LastOpSize instead.

sisLowLastOpSize.name: sisLowLastOpSize
sisLowLastOpSize.description: The total amount of data in KBytes that the last completed SIS operation had processed. This object returns the least significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use sis64LastOpSize instead.

sisLastOpError.name: sisLastOpError
sisLastOpError.description: The error that the last SIS operation encountered if it failed.

sis64LastOpSize.name: sis64LastOpSize
sis64LastOpSize.description: The total amount of data in KBytes that the last completed SIS operation had processed. This object returns all of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

sisIsCompressionEnabled.name: sisIsCompressionEnabled
sisIsCompressionEnabled.description: Indicates whether background compression is enabled on the volume or not.

sisIsInlineEnabled.name: sisIsInlineEnabled
sisIsInlineEnabled.description: Indicates whether inline compression is enabled on the volume or not

sisVserver.name: sisVserver
sisVserver.description: Vserver owning the Storage efficiency volume. This entry is only available from the cluster interface.

sisPolicy.name: sisPolicy
sisPolicy.description: Storage efficiency policy name set on the volume. This entry is only available from the cluster interface.

sisRowAvailable.name: sisRowAvailable
sisRowAvailable.description: Indicates if other fields in this entry are available. This field is returned only from the cluster interfaces. If something goes wrong while fetching the values for fields in this table, the values returned may not be valid. The volume returned may not be a SIS volume. For fields that could not be fetched, default values are set. For integers it is -1, for counters 0, and for string it is null.

sisMinBlocksShared.name: sisMinBlocksShared
sisMinBlocksShared.description: The minimum number of contiguous blocks in a file that will be considered for block sharing. If the number of contiguous duplicate blocks is less than this number, then they won't be considered for sharing.

sisBlocksSkippedSharing.name: sisBlocksSkippedSharing
sisBlocksSkippedSharing.description: Number of blocks not considered for sharing because contiguous duplicate blocks were less than the value set for sisMinBlocksShared.

sisLastSuccessfulOpBeginTime.name: sisLastSuccessfulOpBeginTime
sisLastSuccessfulOpBeginTime.description: The starting time of the last successful SIS operation.

sisLastSuccessfulOpEndTime.name: sisLastSuccessfulOpEndTime
sisLastSuccessfulOpEndTime.description: The ending time of the last successful SIS operation.

sisLastOpState.name: sisLastOpState
sisLastOpState.description: The state of the last SIS operation.

sisLogicalSize.name: sisLogicalSize
sisLogicalSize.description: The size of logical data in the volume in bytes. This may be calculated approximately using these fields in dfTable MIB [df64DedupeSaved + df64CompressSaved + df64SisSharedKBytes * 1024].

sisLogicalLimit.name: sisLogicalLimit
sisLogicalLimit.description: Indicates SIS logical limit for the volume. It is equal to WAFL maximum nominal size of 64bit volume.

sisQueuedJob.name: sisQueuedJob
sisQueuedJob.description: Indicates type of sis operation that is queued for the volume. Possible values: 'scan', 'start', 'check', 'downgrade'.

sisStaleFpPercentage.name: sisStaleFpPercentage
sisStaleFpPercentage.description: Indicates percentage of fingerprints that are stale in the fingerprint database. It can be more than 100%, if blocks are overwritten or deleted.

sisIsIddEnabled.name: sisIsIddEnabled
sisIsIddEnabled.description: Indicates Incompressible data detection is enabled on compressed volume.

sisQuickCheckFsize.name: sisQuickCheckFsize
sisQuickCheckFsize.description: Compression quick check file size. If Incompressible data detection is enabled and if the file size is >= quick-check-fsize, inline compression will do a 4k quick check before doing full CG compression.

sisIsConstituent.name: sisIsConstituent
sisIsConstituent.description: Indicates whether the volume is a constituent or not.

compressIsLicensed.name: compressIsLicensed
compressIsLicensed.description: Indicates whether compression is licensed on the filer.

compressTable.name: compressTable
compressTable.description: Provide a report of the total space used as well as the space saved by compression on volumes.

compressEntry.name: compressEntry
compressEntry.description: Provide a report of the total space used as well as the space saved by compression on the referenced file system.

compressIndex.name: compressIndex
compressIndex.description: A number that identifies this entry for the referenced file system.

compressFileSys.name: compressFileSys
compressFileSys.description: The name for the referenced file system.

compressHighUsedKBytes.name: compressHighUsedKBytes
compressHighUsedKBytes.description: The total disk space in KBytes that is in use on the referenced file system. This object returns the most significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use compress64UsedKBytes instead.

compressLowUsedKBytes.name: compressLowUsedKBytes
compressLowUsedKBytes.description: The total disk space in KBytes that is in use on the referenced file system. This object returns the least significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use compress64UsedKBytes instead.

compress64UsedKBytes.name: compress64UsedKBytes
compress64UsedKBytes.description: The total disk space in KBytes that is in use on the referenced file system. This object returns all of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

compressHighSavedKBytes.name: compressHighSavedKBytes
compressHighSavedKBytes.description: The disk space in KBytes of disk space that is saved by compression on the referenced file system. This object returns the most significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use compress64SavedKBytes instead.

compressLowSavedKBytes.name: compressLowSavedKBytes
compressLowSavedKBytes.description: The disk space in KBytes of disk space that is saved by compression on the referenced filesystem. This object returns the least significant 32 bits of the 64 bit unsigned integer. This object is deprecated - Use compress64SavedKBytes instead.

compress64SavedKBytes.name: compress64SavedKBytes
compress64SavedKBytes.description: The disk space in KBytes of disk space that is saved by compression on the referenced filesystem. This object returns all of the 64 bit unsigned integer.

compressPercentSaved.name: compressPercentSaved
compressPercentSaved.description: The percentage of disk space saved by compression on the referenced filesystem.

extcacheType.name: extcacheType
extcacheType.description: Indicates the type of external cache being used. Examples are none, PCS, IOMEM.

extcacheSubType.name: extcacheSubType
extcacheSubType.description: Indicates the sub-type of external cache being used. Examples are none, PAM1, PAM2.

extcache64Uptime.name: extcache64Uptime
extcache64Uptime.description: Indicates the uptime of the external cache.

extcache64Size.name: extcache64Size
extcache64Size.description: Indicates size of the external cache in bytes.

extcache64Usedsize.name: extcache64Usedsize
extcache64Usedsize.description: Indicates number of bytes used in the external cache.

extcache64TotalBuffers.name: extcache64TotalBuffers
extcache64TotalBuffers.description: Indicates total number of 4k blocks in the external cache.

extcacheOptions.name: extcacheOptions
extcacheOptions.description: Indicates external cache options that are currently turned on.

extcache64Hits.name: extcache64Hits
extcache64Hits.description: Indicates number of wafl buffers read from the external cache

extcache64Misses.name: extcache64Misses
extcache64Misses.description: Indicates the number of external cache misses

extcache64Inserts.name: extcache64Inserts
extcache64Inserts.description: Indicates number of wafl buffers inserted into the external cache

extcache64Evicts.name: extcache64Evicts
extcache64Evicts.description: Indicates the number of buffers evicted from the external cache

extcache64Invalidates.name: extcache64Invalidates
extcache64Invalidates.description: Indicates the number of buffers invalidated in the external cache

extcache64BlocksRef0.name: extcache64BlocksRef0
extcache64BlocksRef0.description: Indicates the number of non-referenced buffers currently in the external cache

extcache64HitNormalL0.name: extcache64HitNormalL0
extcache64HitNormalL0.description: Indicates the number of L0 buffers read from the external cache

extcache64MetaData.name: extcache64MetaData
extcache64MetaData.description: Indicates the number of metadata buffers read from the external cache

extcache64ReadLatency.name: extcache64ReadLatency
extcache64ReadLatency.description: Indicates the average latency of read IOs in the external cache in milliseconds

extcache64WriteLatency.name: extcache64WriteLatency
extcache64WriteLatency.description: Indicates the average latency of write IOs in the external cache in milliseconds

extcache64RCLength.name: extcache64RCLength
extcache64RCLength.description: Indicates the average read chain length in the external cache

extcache64WCLength.name: extcache64WCLength
extcache64WCLength.description: Indicates the average write chain length in the external cache

qosPolicyGroupEntry.name: qosPolicyGroupEntry
qosPolicyGroupEntry.description: Entry for a QoS Policy Group.

qosPolicyGroupVserver.name: qosPolicyGroupVserver
qosPolicyGroupVserver.description: Vserver that the QoS Policy Group belongs to

qosReadaheadDefault.name: qosReadaheadDefault
qosReadaheadDefault.description: Indicates if this is the default Read-Ahead Setting.

qosReadaheadMaxRange.name: qosReadaheadMaxRange
qosReadaheadMaxRange.description: Maximum Range Used When Aging Streams (Blocks.

qosReadaheadMinRange.name: qosReadaheadMinRange
qosReadaheadMinRange.description: Minimum Range Used When Aging Streams (Blocks).

qosReadaheadDiskResponseWeight.name: qosReadaheadDiskResponseWeight
qosReadaheadDiskResponseWeight.description: Weight for Disk Response Time Aging (%).

qosReadaheadMetadataBlocks.name: qosReadaheadMetadataBlocks
qosReadaheadMetadataBlocks.description: Minimum Blocks for Which Metadata is Predicted.

qosReadaheadEarlyCount.name: qosReadaheadEarlyCount
qosReadaheadEarlyCount.description: Number of IO Operations Cautiously Predicted.

qosReadaheadMinRetireTime.name: qosReadaheadMinRetireTime
qosReadaheadMinRetireTime.description: Minimum Time Before a Stream is Retired (us)

qosReadaheadMaxRetireTime.name: qosReadaheadMaxRetireTime
qosReadaheadMaxRetireTime.description: Maximum Time Before a Stream is Retired (us)

userDefined.name: userDefined
userDefined.description: A polling-style trap built using the 'snmp traps' command on the filer.

dhmNoticeDegradedIO.name: dhmNoticeDegradedIO
dhmNoticeDegradedIO.description: Disk Health Monitor - Reported a Disk Degraded-I/O Event

dhmNoticePFAEvent.name: dhmNoticePFAEvent
dhmNoticePFAEvent.description: Disk Health Monitor - Reported a Disk Predictive-Failure Event

emergencyTrap.name: emergencyTrap
emergencyTrap.description: A user-defined trap indicating an extremely urgent situation, usually indicating that the system has failed and is shutting down.

alertTrap.name: alertTrap
alertTrap.description: A user-defined trap indicating a condition that should be corrected immediately, such as a failed disk.

criticalTrap.name: criticalTrap
criticalTrap.description: A user-defined trap indicating a critical condition, such as a hard device error.

errorTrap.name: errorTrap
errorTrap.description: A user-defined trap indicating an error condition, such as a mistake in a configuration file.

warningTrap.name: warningTrap
warningTrap.description: A user-defined trap indicating a condition which is not an error, but which may require special handling.

notificationTrap.name: notificationTrap
notificationTrap.description: A user-defined trap meant to provide notification, such as an hourly uptime message.

informationalTrap.name: informationalTrap
informationalTrap.description: A user-defined trap used for informational purposes.

dbgTrap.name: dbgTrap
dbgTrap.description: A user-defined trap used for debugging purposes. This trap was previously mis-documented as being trap number 17, with the name debugTrap. It has always, actually, been trap 18. The name change is to avoid issues with environments that already have a record for debugTrap.

diskFailedShutdown.name: diskFailedShutdown
diskFailedShutdown.description: System is shutting down because the system has been running in degraded mode for 24 hours. The trap includes a string describing the failed disk.

diskFailed.name: diskFailed
diskFailed.description: One or more disks failed. The trap includes a string describing the failed disk(s).

diskRepaired.name: diskRepaired
diskRepaired.description: The failed disks have been repaired. This trap is a placeholder - it is not currently sent by Data ONTAP.

fanFailureShutdown.name: fanFailureShutdown
fanFailureShutdown.description: Critical chassis or cpu fans have failed and the system is shutting down.

fanFailed.name: fanFailed
fanFailed.description: One or more chassis fans failed. The trap includes a string describing the failed fan(s).

fanWarning.name: fanWarning
fanWarning.description: One or more chassis or cpu fans are in warning state. The trap includes a string describing the fan(s) in the warning state.

powerSupplyFailureShutdown.name: powerSupplyFailureShutdown
powerSupplyFailureShutdown.description: Critical power supplies or power rails failed and the system is shutting down.

powerSupplyFailed.name: powerSupplyFailed
powerSupplyFailed.description: One or more redundant power supplies failed. Include in the trap a string describing the failed power supply(ies).

powerSupplyWarning.name: powerSupplyWarning
powerSupplyWarning.description: One or more power supplies or power rails in warning state. Include in the trap a string describing the power supply(ies) or the power rail(s) in the warning state.

powerSupplyRepaired.name: powerSupplyRepaired
powerSupplyRepaired.description: Previously-failed power supplies or power rails have been repaired.

cpuTooBusy.name: cpuTooBusy
cpuTooBusy.description: CPU utilization exceeds 90%. This trap is not enabled by default. To enable this trap set the registry entry options.monitor.cpu.enable to on. Note that as the threshold for this trap is checked once a minute it is possible to receive multiple instances of this trap in a short time.

cpuOk.name: cpuOk
cpuOk.description: CPU utilization has dropped back below 90%.

nvramBatteryDischarged.name: nvramBatteryDischarged
nvramBatteryDischarged.description: The NVRAM battery is fully discharged.

nvramBatteryLow.name: nvramBatteryLow
nvramBatteryLow.description: The charge in the NVRAM battery is low.

clusterNodeFailed.name: clusterNodeFailed
clusterNodeFailed.description: A node in a Cluster FailOver configuration failed. Its partner will assume service for the failed node.

clusterNodeTakenOver.name: clusterNodeTakenOver
clusterNodeTakenOver.description: The partner has taken over for a failed cluster node.

clusterNodeRepaired.name: clusterNodeRepaired
clusterNodeRepaired.description: A cluster node has resumed operation.

clusterNodeRepairing.name: clusterNodeRepairing
clusterNodeRepairing.description: A cluster node has rebooted, and a giveback has started.

volumeFull.name: volumeFull
volumeFull.description: At least one volume is more than 98% full. The string sent with the trap gives the name of the volume or volumes which exceed the volumeFull or volumeNearlyFull thresholds

volumeNearlyFull.name: volumeNearlyFull
volumeNearlyFull.description: At least one volume is more than 95% full. The string sent with the trap gives the name of the volume or volumes which exceed the volumeFull or volumeNearlyFull thresholds

volumeRepaired.name: volumeRepaired
volumeRepaired.description: All volumes are now under 95% full.

volumesStillFull.name: volumesStillFull
volumesStillFull.description: At least one volume that was full or nearly full is now OK, but more volumes still exceed the volumeNearlyFull or volumeFull thresholds. This trap is generally sent within a short time of when a volume becomes OK, though if two volumes become OK within this timeframe, only one trap is sent. The string sent with the trap gives the name of the volume or volumes which still exceed the volumeFull or volumeNearlyFull thresholds. It does not send the name of any volume that is OK.

overTempShutdown.name: overTempShutdown
overTempShutdown.description: System temperature is too high to continue operating. The system is shutting down.

overTemp.name: overTemp
overTemp.description: System temperature is too high and in the warning level.

overTempRepaired.name: overTempRepaired
overTempRepaired.description: System temperature has returned to an acceptable value.

shelfFault.name: shelfFault
shelfFault.description: A disk storage shelf reported a fault, probably due to a problem with drive placement, fans, power, or temperature.

shelfRepaired.name: shelfRepaired
shelfRepaired.description: A previously-reported shelf fault is now corrected.

globalStatusNonRecoverable.name: globalStatusNonRecoverable
globalStatusNonRecoverable.description: The appliance's overall status changed to 'nonRecoverable', indicating a problem so severe that the appliance is shutting down.

globalStatusCritical.name: globalStatusCritical
globalStatusCritical.description: The appliance's overall status changed to 'critical', indicating a problem that needs immediate attention.

globalStatusNonCritical.name: globalStatusNonCritical
globalStatusNonCritical.description: The appliance's overall status changed to 'nonCritical', indicating a problem that needs attention.

globalStatusOk.name: globalStatusOk
globalStatusOk.description: The appliance's overall status returned to normal.

softQuotaExceeded.name: softQuotaExceeded
softQuotaExceeded.description: A user has exceeded their soft quota limit.

softQuotaNormal.name: softQuotaNormal
softQuotaNormal.description: A user is safely back under their soft quota limit.

autosupportSendError.name: autosupportSendError
autosupportSendError.description: Unable to send auto support. The trap includes a string describing the reason for the failure.

autosupportConfigurationError.name: autosupportConfigurationError
autosupportConfigurationError.description: Auto support may be configured incorrectly. The trap includes a string describing the mis-configuration.

upsLinePowerOff.name: upsLinePowerOff
upsLinePowerOff.description: UPS: Input line power has failed and UPS is now on battery.

upsBatteryCritical.name: upsBatteryCritical
upsBatteryCritical.description: UPS: Battery is nearly exhausted, starting graceful shutdown.

upsShuttingDown.name: upsShuttingDown
upsShuttingDown.description: UPS: Shutting down now: Time left on battery is exhausted.

upsBatteryWarning.name: upsBatteryWarning
upsBatteryWarning.description: UPS: Warning: Time left on battery is getting critical.

upsLinePowerRestored.name: upsLinePowerRestored
upsLinePowerRestored.description: UPS: Input line power has been restored and UPS is now off battery.

appEmergency.name: appEmergency
appEmergency.description: The application encountered an extremely urgent situation and requires an immediate response.

appAlert.name: appAlert
appAlert.description: The application is in a condition that should be corrected immediately.

appCritical.name: appCritical
appCritical.description: The application encountered a critical condition.

appError.name: appError
appError.description: The application encountered an error condition.

appWarning.name: appWarning
appWarning.description: The application is in a condition which is not an error, but which may require special handling.

appNotice.name: appNotice
appNotice.description: The application is notifying of a certain event.

appInfo.name: appInfo
appInfo.description: The application's message is meant for informational purposes.

appTrap.name: appTrap
appTrap.description: The application requires to be debugged.

alfFilewrap.name: alfFilewrap
alfFilewrap.description: The internal audit file has wrapped. You are currently losing event records. Warning the user.

alfFileSaved.name: alfFileSaved
alfFileSaved.description: The internal audit log has been auto saved to an external evt file. Notifying the user.

alfFileNearlyFull.name: alfFileNearlyFull
alfFileNearlyFull.description: The internal audit log file is nearly full. The file is going to wrap. Notifying the user.

quotaExceeded.name: quotaExceeded
quotaExceeded.description: One of the quota limits has been exceeded. The trap includes a string describing the specific event which triggered the trap. The string is structured in the following form: Quota Event: status=exceeded, type={hard|soft|threshold}, user={username}, volume={volume}, limit_item={files|disk}, limit_value={#files|#kilobytes} [ , treeid={tree-id} ] [ , vfiler={vfiler} ] An example of a complete message would be: Quota Event: status=exceeded, type=soft, user=admin, volume=vol1, limit_item=disk, limit_value=1000000, treeid=8 Additional key=value items may, in the future, be appended to this message.

quotaNormal.name: quotaNormal
quotaNormal.description: One of the quota limits has gone back down to a normal level. The trap includes a string describing the specific event which triggered the trap. The string is structured in the following form: Quota Event: status=normal, type={hard|soft|threshold}, user={username}, volume={volume}, limit_item={files|disk}, limit_value={#files|#kilobytes} [ , treeid={tree-id} ] [ , vfiler={vfiler} ] An example of a complete message would be: Quota Event: status=normal, type=soft, user=admin, volume=vol1, limit_item=disk, limit_value=1000000, treeid=8 Additional key=value items may, in the future, be appended to this message.

waflDirFull.name: waflDirFull
waflDirFull.description: The directory has been filled to its limit

eccSummary.name: eccSummary
eccSummary.description: Memory ECC: number of new correctable ECC errors

eccMasked.name: eccMasked
eccMasked.description: Memory ECC: High frequency of ECC errors

ftpdMaxConnNotice.name: ftpdMaxConnNotice
ftpdMaxConnNotice.description: Ftp daemon: number of connections hits maximum number

ftpdMaxConnThresholdNotice.name: ftpdMaxConnThresholdNotice
ftpdMaxConnThresholdNotice.description: Ftp daemon: number of connections nearly hits maximum number

scsitgtFCPLinkBreak.name: scsitgtFCPLinkBreak
scsitgtFCPLinkBreak.description: SCSI Target: Link Break on FCP adapter

scsitgtPartnerPathMisconfigured.name: scsitgtPartnerPathMisconfigured
scsitgtPartnerPathMisconfigured.description: SCSI Target: FCP Partner Path Misconfigured

scsitgtThrottleNotice.name: scsitgtThrottleNotice
scsitgtThrottleNotice.description: SCSI Target: Throttle limit event notification

vifPrimaryLinkFailed.name: vifPrimaryLinkFailed
vifPrimaryLinkFailed.description: Vif: The primary Interface on a Single mode vif has failed

vifAllLinksFailed.name: vifAllLinksFailed
vifAllLinksFailed.description: Vif: All the links of the vif have failed

vscanVirusDetectedError.name: vscanVirusDetectedError
vscanVirusDetectedError.description: VScan: A virus scanner has detected a virus on the Filer

vscanDisConnection.name: vscanDisConnection
vscanDisConnection.description: VScan: A virus scanner has dropped its connection from the Filer

vscanConfigurationChange.name: vscanConfigurationChange
vscanConfigurationChange.description: VScan: There has been a change to the vscan configuration

vscanConnection.name: vscanConnection
vscanConnection.description: VScan: A virus scanner has made a connection to the Filer

vscanServerUpgrade.name: vscanServerUpgrade
vscanServerUpgrade.description: VScan: The Vscan server has been upgraded

volumeRestrictedByMirrorBigIo.name: volumeRestrictedByMirrorBigIo
volumeRestrictedByMirrorBigIo.description: A volume that experienced a medium error during reconstruction is restricted and marked wafl-inconsistent, but starting wafliron has failed. This trap is issued to alert operator that a volume is not accessible and wafliron must be started to allow access to it.

volumeInconsistentUmount.name: volumeInconsistentUmount
volumeInconsistentUmount.description: This trap is issued when we unmount a volume due to an inconsistency.

volumeStateChanged.name: volumeStateChanged
volumeStateChanged.description: Volume is being taken offline or being restricted. The string sent with trap specifies name of affected volume and its state.

volumeOnline.name: volumeOnline
volumeOnline.description: Volume is online now. The string sent with trap specifies name of volume which is online now.

rmcCardNeedsReplacement.name: rmcCardNeedsReplacement
rmcCardNeedsReplacement.description: Remote Management Controller card needs replacement. The trap includes a string specifying the reason for replacement

rmcCardMissingCables.name: rmcCardMissingCables
rmcCardMissingCables.description: Remote Management Controller card is missing its internal cable, or LAN cable or power supply cable. The trap includes a string specifying the missing component.

volumeRemoteUnreachable.name: volumeRemoteUnreachable
volumeRemoteUnreachable.description: Local volume encountered an error while communicating to remote volume.

volumeRemoteOk.name: volumeRemoteOk
volumeRemoteOk.description: The communication between remote volume and local volume returned to normal.

volumeRemoteRestored.name: volumeRemoteRestored
volumeRemoteRestored.description: The data on remote volume has been fully restored to local volume.

volumeRemoteRestoreBegin.name: volumeRemoteRestoreBegin
volumeRemoteRestoreBegin.description: The data on remote volume has started being restored to local volume by Restore-on-Demand.

volumeRestrictedRootConflict.name: volumeRestrictedRootConflict
volumeRestrictedRootConflict.description: Volume is restricted due to a root volume conflict. The string sent with trap specifies name of conflicting volume which is being restricted.

volumeOfflineTooBig.name: volumeOfflineTooBig
volumeOfflineTooBig.description: Volume cannot be brought online because its raw size is larger than maximum allowed size. The string sent with trap specifies name of affected volume and its raw size, and maximum allowed size.

volumeOffline.name: volumeOffline
volumeOffline.description: Volume is being taken offline. The string sent with trap specifies name of affected volume and reason for being taken offline.

volumeRestricted.name: volumeRestricted
volumeRestricted.description: Volume is being restricted. The string sent with trap specifies name of affected volume and reason for being restricted.

volumeDegradedDirty.name: volumeDegradedDirty
volumeDegradedDirty.description: Volume is degraded and has dirty parity. WAFL_check must be run on this volume before it can be brought online. The string sent with trap specifies name of affected volume.

volumeError.name: volumeError
volumeError.description: This trap is issued when a volume cannot be brought online due to an error. The string sent with trap specifies name of affected volume and error description.

volumeSelectedRootConflict.name: volumeSelectedRootConflict
volumeSelectedRootConflict.description: This trap is issued when multiple root volumes are detected at boot time and one is selected as the root by default. The string sent with the trap specifies the name of the selected volume and the reason.

snapmirrorSyncFailed.name: snapmirrorSyncFailed
snapmirrorSyncFailed.description: Synchronous SnapMirror failed and went into asynchronous mode.

snapmirrorSyncOk.name: snapmirrorSyncOk
snapmirrorSyncOk.description: Synchronous SnapMirror went into synchronous mode.

chassisTemperatureShutdown.name: chassisTemperatureShutdown
chassisTemperatureShutdown.description: The chassis temperature is extreme. The appliance has initiated a shutdown to protect itself. The operating environment should be monitored and corrected before restarting the appliance.

chassisTemperatureWarning.name: chassisTemperatureWarning
chassisTemperatureWarning.description: The chassis temperature is either too high or too low. The temperature should be monitored and, if possible, corrected.

chassisTemperatureUnknown.name: chassisTemperatureUnknown
chassisTemperatureUnknown.description: The chassis temperature is unknown, because reading can't be obtained from the chassis temperature sensor.

chassisCPUFanStopped.name: chassisCPUFanStopped
chassisCPUFanStopped.description: One or more CPU fans have stopped. The appliance has initiated a shutdown to protect itself. A new motherboard may be required to correct the fan. Contact customer support for direction.

chassisCPUFanSlow.name: chassisCPUFanSlow
chassisCPUFanSlow.description: A CPU fan is spinning too slowly. A new motherboard may be required to correct the fan. Contact customer support for direction.

chassisCPUFanOk.name: chassisCPUFanOk
chassisCPUFanOk.description: All CPU fan(s) are properly functioning.

chassisPowerSupplyDegraded.name: chassisPowerSupplyDegraded
chassisPowerSupplyDegraded.description: One or more chassis power supplies are degraded. A description of the degraded state has been logged to the console and message log file.

chassisPowerSupplyRemoved.name: chassisPowerSupplyRemoved
chassisPowerSupplyRemoved.description: One or more chassis power supplies are removed.

chassisPowerSupplyOff.name: chassisPowerSupplyOff
chassisPowerSupplyOff.description: One or more chassis power supplies are off.

chassisPowerSuppliesOk.name: chassisPowerSuppliesOk
chassisPowerSuppliesOk.description: The chassis power supplies are all functioning properly.

chassisPowerSupplyOk.name: chassisPowerSupplyOk
chassisPowerSupplyOk.description: This chassis power supply is functioning properly.

chassisPowerDegraded.name: chassisPowerDegraded
chassisPowerDegraded.description: The power within the chassis is degraded. A description of the degraded state has been logged to the console and message log file.

chassisPowerOk.name: chassisPowerOk
chassisPowerOk.description: The power within the chassis is functioning properly.

chassisFanDegraded.name: chassisFanDegraded
chassisFanDegraded.description: A chassis fan has been degraded.

chassisFanRemoved.name: chassisFanRemoved
chassisFanRemoved.description: A chassis fan FRU has been removed.

chassisFanStopped.name: chassisFanStopped
chassisFanStopped.description: One or more chassis fans have stopped.

chassisFanWarning.name: chassisFanWarning
chassisFanWarning.description: One or more chassis fans is spinning slowly or too fast.

chassisFanOk.name: chassisFanOk
chassisFanOk.description: All chassis fans are functioning properly.

writeVerificationFailed.name: writeVerificationFailed
writeVerificationFailed.description: A write has failed a verification test on a SnapValidator enabled volume.

prefDCDisconnect.name: prefDCDisconnect
prefDCDisconnect.description: All connections to domain controllers in the preferred domain controllers list have been lost.

domainControllerDisconnect.name: domainControllerDisconnect
domainControllerDisconnect.description: A CIFS domain controller connection to the filer has failed.

dcPasswdChangeFailed.name: dcPasswdChangeFailed
dcPasswdChangeFailed.description: An attempt to change the storage system's password with the domain controller has failed.

domainControllerConnected.name: domainControllerConnected
domainControllerConnected.description: A CIFS domain controller connection to the filer has been established.

plexFailed.name: plexFailed
plexFailed.description: This trap is issued when one plex of a mirrored traditional volume or aggregate is failed. The string sent with this trap specifies name of affected plex or mirrored traditional volume or aggregate.

plexOffline.name: plexOffline
plexOffline.description: This trap is issued when a plex becomes offline. The string sent with this trap specifies name of affected plex or mirrored traditional volume or aggregate.

shelfSESElectronicsFailed.name: shelfSESElectronicsFailed
shelfSESElectronicsFailed.description: One or more of the enclosure services devices in a disk shelf has failed. Some shelf designs combine the enclosure monitoring hardware function into the module that provides the storage interface to the shelf. A failure in the enclosure monitoring section of these combined modules does not necessarily indicate a failure in disk or loop or bus operation, which may be able to continue.

shelfSESElectronicsInfo.name: shelfSESElectronicsInfo
shelfSESElectronicsInfo.description: A previously reported failure of an enclosure services device in a disk shelf has been corrected, or the device has reported information that does not necessarily require customer action.

shelfIFModuleFailed.name: shelfIFModuleFailed
shelfIFModuleFailed.description: One or more of the storage interface modules in a disk shelf has failed. Some shelf designs combine the enclosure monitoring hardware function into the module that operates the fibre channel loop or SCSI in the shelf. This failure is of the storage interface itself, not a failure of the enclosure monitoring, which may be able to continue. This failure may make one or more disks in the shelf or in the loop or bus unavailable.

shelfIFModuleWarning.name: shelfIFModuleWarning
shelfIFModuleWarning.description: One or more of the storage interface modules in a disk shelf has a warning condition. Some shelf designs combine the enclosure monitoring hardware function into the module that operates the fibre channel loop or SCSI in the shelf. This warning condition is of the storage interface itself, not a failure of the enclosure monitoring, which may be able to continue.

shelfIFModuleInfo.name: shelfIFModuleInfo
shelfIFModuleInfo.description: A previously reported failure of a disk shelf interface module has been corrected, or the module has reported information that does not necessarily require customer action.

maxDirSizeAlert.name: maxDirSizeAlert
maxDirSizeAlert.description: A directory has reached its maxdirsize limit. Either increase the maxdirsize or clean up the directory.

maxDirSizeWarning.name: maxDirSizeWarning
maxDirSizeWarning.description: A directory is getting close to its maxdirsize limit. Either increase the maxdirsize or clean up the directory.

cifsStatsExhaustMemCtrlBlk.name: cifsStatsExhaustMemCtrlBlk
cifsStatsExhaustMemCtrlBlk.description: A request for a CIFS control block cannot be granted. All control blocks are in use.

chassisPSRemovedxMinShutdown.name: chassisPSRemovedxMinShutdown
chassisPSRemovedxMinShutdown.description: Power Supply Unit is removed from the system. System will be shutdown in x minutes if it is not put back.

chassisPSUsMismatch.name: chassisPSUsMismatch
chassisPSUsMismatch.description: Power Supply Units in the system are of different type. Please replace them with correct Power Supply Units.

chassisFanFailxMinShutdown.name: chassisFanFailxMinShutdown
chassisFanFailxMinShutdown.description: Multiple chassis fan failure. System will shut down in a few minutes if not corrected.

chassisPSUwrongInput.name: chassisPSUwrongInput
chassisPSUwrongInput.description: Power Supply Unit (PSU) in the system is connected to an incompatible external power source. Please change the power source being used or replace the PSU with one that matches the current power source.

powerSupplyFanFailxMinShutdown.name: powerSupplyFanFailxMinShutdown
powerSupplyFanFailxMinShutdown.description: Multiple power supply fans failure. System will shut down in a few minutes if not corrected.

remoteSystemMgtAlert.name: remoteSystemMgtAlert
remoteSystemMgtAlert.description: system remote management detected a system down event. The trap includes a string describing the specific event which triggered the trap. The string is structured in the following form: Remote Management Event: type={system_down|system_up|test|keep_alive}, severity={alert|warning|notice|normal|debug|info}, event={post_error|watchdog_reset|power_loss|abnormal_reboot}, key=value An example of a complete message would be: Remote Management Event: type=system_down, severity=alert, event=watchdog_reset, ss=16bytes Additional key=value items may, in the future, be appended to this message. The events that would generate this trap would be: post_error: Fatal POST error on boot power_loss: Loss of power to system abnormal_reboot: l2_watchdog_reset

remoteSystemMgmtWarning.name: remoteSystemMgmtWarning
remoteSystemMgmtWarning.description: system remote management detected a system down event. The trap includes a string describing the specific event which triggered the trap. The string is structured in the following form: Remote Management Event: type={system_down|system_up|test|keep_alive}, severity={alert|warning|notice|normal|debug|info}, event={loss-of-heartbeat}, key=value An example of a complete message would be: Remote Management Event: type=system_down, severity=warning, event=loss_of_heartbeat, ss=16bytes Additional key=value items may, in the future, be appended to this message. The events that would generate this trap would be: loss_of_heartbeat: Loss of heartbeat to the RLM.

remoteSystemMgmtNotification.name: remoteSystemMgmtNotification
remoteSystemMgmtNotification.description: system remote management detected a system down event. The trap includes a string describing the specific event which triggered the trap. The string is structured in the following form: Remote Management Event: type={system_down|system_up|test|keep_alive}, severity={alert|warning|notice|normal|debug|info}, event={power_off_via_rlm,power_cycle_via_rlm,reset_via_rlm}, key=value An example of a complete message would be: Remote Management Event: type=system_down, severity=notice, event=power_off_via_rlm, ss=16bytes Additional key=value items may, in the future, be appended to this message. The events that would generate this trap would be: power_off_via_rlm: This indicates system power off power_cycle_via_rlm: This indicates system power cycle reset_via_rlm: This indicates system reset.

remoteSystemMgmtPeriodic.name: remoteSystemMgmtPeriodic
remoteSystemMgmtPeriodic.description: This is a periodic keep alive from system remote management. The trap includes a string describing the specific event which triggered the trap. The string is structured in the following form: Remote Management Event: type={system_down|system_up|test|keep_alive}, severity={alert|warning|notice|normal|debug|info}, event={periodic_message} An example of a complete message would be: Remote Management Event: type=keep_alive, severity=info, event=periodic_message Additional key=value items may, in the future, be appended to this message.

remotesystemMgmtTest.name: remotesystemMgmtTest
remotesystemMgmtTest.description: This is a test trap from system remote management. The trap includes a string describing the specific event which triggered the trap. The string is structured in the following form: Remote Management Event: type={system_down|system_up|test|keep_alive}, severity={alert|warning|notice|normal|debug|info}, event={periodic_message} An example of a complete message would be: Remote Management Event: type=test, severity=notice, event=test Additional key=value items may, in the future, be appended to this message.

diskMultipathOneSwitch.name: diskMultipathOneSwitch
diskMultipathOneSwitch.description: A multipathed disk is only connected to one switch.

diskMultipathNoTakeover.name: diskMultipathNoTakeover
diskMultipathNoTakeover.description: Multipath disks or luns could not be detected for the partner. The node will be unable to takeover correctly.

diskMultipathWarning.name: diskMultipathWarning
diskMultipathWarning.description: Synchronous mirroring is enabled, even though disks are not multipathed.

driveDisableErr.name: driveDisableErr
driveDisableErr.description: A drive has been disabled by the shelf module due to hardware errors. If it is the only drive in the shelf that is disabled, replace the drive.

hbaOfflineInformation.name: hbaOfflineInformation
hbaOfflineInformation.description: A host bus adapter (HBA) port has been disabled. This state may be caused either by user command or by errors that make the interface unable to communicate with attached devices.

timedTargetNotResponding.name: timedTargetNotResponding
timedTargetNotResponding.description: NTP Time Daemon lost contact with the configured target

svBackupSnapWarningLimit.name: svBackupSnapWarningLimit
svBackupSnapWarningLimit.description: The remaining number of Snapshot copies for a backup schedule is below warning limit specified.

avTrendLicenseExpired.name: avTrendLicenseExpired
avTrendLicenseExpired.description: Trend Micro antivirus license has expired
